3279 
3280 static Attribute
3281 foldDenseElementsAttrDestInsertOp(InsertOp insertOp, Attribute srcAttr,
3282  Attribute dstAttr,
3283  int64_t maxVectorSizeFoldThreshold) {
3284  if (insertOp.hasDynamicPosition())
3285  return {};
3286 
3287  auto denseDst = llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(dstAttr);
3288  if (!denseDst)
3289  return {};
3290 
3291  if (!srcAttr) {
3292  return {};
3293  }
3294 
3295  VectorType destTy = insertOp.getDestVectorType();
3296  if (destTy.isScalable())
3297  return {};
3298 
3299  // Make sure we do not create too many large constants.
3300  if (destTy.getNumElements() > maxVectorSizeFoldThreshold &&
3301  !insertOp->hasOneUse())
3302  return {};
3303 
3304  // Calculate the linearized position of the continuous chunk of elements to
3305  // insert.
3306  llvm::SmallVector<int64_t> completePositions(destTy.getRank(), 0);
3307  copy(insertOp.getStaticPosition(), completePositions.begin());
3308  int64_t insertBeginPosition =
3309  linearize(completePositions, computeStrides(destTy.getShape()));
3310 
3311  SmallVector<Attribute> insertedValues;
3312  Type destEltType = destTy.getElementType();
3313 
3314  /// Converts the expected type to an IntegerAttr if there's
3315  /// a mismatch.
3316  if (auto denseSource = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseElementsAttr>(srcAttr)) {
3317  for (auto value : denseSource.getValues<Attribute>())
3318  insertedValues.push_back(convertIntegerAttr(value, destEltType));
3319  } else {
3320  insertedValues.push_back(convertIntegerAttr(srcAttr, destEltType));
3321  }
3322 
3323  auto allValues = llvm::to_vector(denseDst.getValues<Attribute>());
3324  copy(insertedValues, allValues.begin() + insertBeginPosition);
3325  auto newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(destTy, allValues);
3326 
3327  return newAttr;
3328 }
3329 
3330 /// Folder to replace the `dest` operand of the insert op with the root dest of
3331 /// the insert op use chain.
3332 static Value foldInsertUseChain(InsertOp insertOp) {
3333  auto destInsert = insertOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertOp>();
3334  if (!destInsert)
3335  return {};
3336 
3337  if (insertOp.getMixedPosition() != destInsert.getMixedPosition())
3338  return {};
3339 
3340  insertOp.setOperand(1, destInsert.getDest());
3341  return insertOp.getResult();
3342 }
3343 
3344 void InsertOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
3345  MLIRContext *context) {
3346  results.add<InsertToBroadcast, BroadcastFolder, InsertSplatToSplat>(context);
3347 }
3348 
3349 OpFoldResult InsertOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
3350  // Do not create constants with more than `vectorSizeFoldThreashold` elements,
3351  // unless the source vector constant has a single use.
3352  constexpr int64_t vectorSizeFoldThreshold = 256;
3353  // Fold "vector.insert %v, %dest [] : vector<2x2xf32> from vector<2x2xf32>" to
3354  // %v. Note: Do not fold "vector.insert %v, %dest [] : f32 into vector<f32>"
3355  // (type mismatch).
3356  if (getNumIndices() == 0 && getValueToStoreType() == getType())
3357  return getValueToStore();
3358  // Fold `arith.constant` indices into the `vector.insert` operation.
3359  // Do not stop here as this fold may enable subsequent folds that require
3360  // constant indices.
3361  SmallVector<Value> operands = {getValueToStore(), getDest()};
3362  auto inplaceFolded = extractInsertFoldConstantOp(*this, adaptor, operands);
3363 
3364  if (auto res = foldInsertUseChain(*this))
3365  return res;
3366  if (auto res = foldPoisonIndexInsertExtractOp(
3367  getContext(), adaptor.getStaticPosition(), kPoisonIndex))
3368  return res;
3369  if (auto res = foldDenseElementsAttrDestInsertOp(
3370  *this, adaptor.getValueToStore(), adaptor.getDest(),
3371  vectorSizeFoldThreshold)) {
3372  return res;
3373  }
3374 
3375  return inplaceFolded;
3376 }

3382 void InsertStridedSliceOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,

3389  result.addTypes(dest.getType());
3390  result.addAttribute(InsertStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName(result.name),
3391  offsetsAttr);
3392  result.addAttribute(InsertStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName(result.name),
3393  stridesAttr);
3394 }

3396 // TODO: Should be moved to Tablegen ConfinedAttr attributes.
3397 template <typename OpType>
3398 static LogicalResult isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(OpType op,
3399  ArrayAttr arrayAttr,
3400  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape,
3401  StringRef attrName) {
3402  if (arrayAttr.size() > shape.size())
3403  return op.emitOpError("expected ")
3404  << attrName << " attribute of rank no greater than vector rank";
3405  return success();
3406 }
3407 
3408 // Returns true if all integers in `arrayAttr` are in the half-open [min, max}
3409 // interval. If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max).
3410 // Otherwise, the admissible interval is [min, max].
3411 template <typename OpType>
3412 static LogicalResult
3413 isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr, int64_t min,
3414  int64_t max, StringRef attrName,
3415  bool halfOpen = true) {
3416  for (auto attr : arrayAttr) {
3417  auto val = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(attr).getInt();
3418  auto upper = max;
3419  if (!halfOpen)
3420  upper += 1;
3421  if (val < min || val >= upper)
3422  return op.emitOpError("expected ") << attrName << " to be confined to ["
3423  << min << ", " << upper << ")";
3424  }
3425  return success();
3426 }
3427 
3428 // Returns true if all integers in `arrayAttr` are in the half-open [min, max}
3429 // interval. If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max).
3430 // Otherwise, the admissible interval is [min, max].
3431 template <typename OpType>
3432 static LogicalResult
3433 isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr,
3434  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape, StringRef attrName,
3435  bool halfOpen = true, int64_t min = 0) {
3436  for (auto [index, attrDimPair] :
3437  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip_first(arrayAttr, shape))) {
3438  int64_t val = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<0>(attrDimPair)).getInt();
3439  int64_t max = std::get<1>(attrDimPair);
3440  if (!halfOpen)
3441  max += 1;
3442  if (val < min || val >= max)
3443  return op.emitOpError("expected ")
3444  << attrName << " dimension " << index << " to be confined to ["
3445  << min << ", " << max << ")";
3446  }
3447  return success();
3448 }
3449 
3450 // Returns true if, for all indices i = 0..shape.size()-1, val is in the
3451 // [min, max} interval:
3452 // val = `arrayAttr1[i]` + `arrayAttr2[i]`,
3453 // If `halfOpen` is true then the admissible interval is [min, max). Otherwise,
3454 // the admissible interval is [min, max].
3455 template <typename OpType>
3456 static LogicalResult isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(
3457  OpType op, ArrayAttr arrayAttr1, ArrayAttr arrayAttr2,
3458  ArrayRef<int64_t> shape, StringRef attrName1, StringRef attrName2,
3459  bool halfOpen = true, int64_t min = 1) {
3460  assert(arrayAttr1.size() <= shape.size());
3461  assert(arrayAttr2.size() <= shape.size());
3462  for (auto [index, it] :
3463  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip(arrayAttr1, arrayAttr2, shape))) {
3464  auto val1 = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<0>(it)).getInt();
3465  auto val2 = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(std::get<1>(it)).getInt();
3466  int64_t max = std::get<2>(it);
3467  if (!halfOpen)
3468  max += 1;
3469  if (val1 + val2 < 0 || val1 + val2 >= max)
3470  return op.emitOpError("expected sum(")
3471  << attrName1 << ", " << attrName2 << ") dimension " << index
3472  << " to be confined to [" << min << ", " << max << ")";
3473  }
3474  return success();
3475 }
3476 
3477 static ArrayAttr makeI64ArrayAttr(ArrayRef<int64_t> values,
3478  MLIRContext *context) {
3479  auto attrs = llvm::map_range(values, [context](int64_t v) -> Attribute {
3480  return IntegerAttr::get(IntegerType::get(context, 64), APInt(64, v));
3481  });
3482  return ArrayAttr::get(context, llvm::to_vector<8>(attrs));
3483 }
3484 
3485 LogicalResult InsertStridedSliceOp::verify() {
3486  auto sourceVectorType = getSourceVectorType();
3487  auto destVectorType = getDestVectorType();
3488  auto offsets = getOffsetsAttr();
3489  auto strides = getStridesAttr();
3490  if (offsets.size() != static_cast<unsigned>(destVectorType.getRank()))
3491  return emitOpError(
3492  "expected offsets of same size as destination vector rank");
3493  if (strides.size() != static_cast<unsigned>(sourceVectorType.getRank()))
3494  return emitOpError("expected strides of same size as source vector rank");
3495  if (sourceVectorType.getRank() > destVectorType.getRank())
3496  return emitOpError(
3497  "expected source rank to be no greater than destination rank");
3498 
3499  auto sourceShape = sourceVectorType.getShape();
3500  auto destShape = destVectorType.getShape();
3501  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sourceShapeAsDestShape(
3502  destShape.size() - sourceShape.size(), 0);
3503  sourceShapeAsDestShape.append(sourceShape.begin(), sourceShape.end());
3504  auto offName = InsertStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName();
3505  auto stridesName = InsertStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName();
3506  if (failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, destShape,
3507  offName)) ||
3508  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(*this, strides, /*min=*/1,
3509  /*max=*/1, stridesName,
3510  /*halfOpen=*/false)) ||
3511  failed(isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(
3512  *this, offsets,
3513  makeI64ArrayAttr(sourceShapeAsDestShape, getContext()), destShape,
3514  offName, "source vector shape",
3515  /*halfOpen=*/false, /*min=*/1)))
3516  return failure();
3517 
3518  unsigned rankDiff = destShape.size() - sourceShape.size();
3519  for (unsigned idx = 0; idx < sourceShape.size(); ++idx) {
3520  if (sourceVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx] !=
3521  destVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx + rankDiff]) {
3522  return emitOpError("mismatching scalable flags (at source vector idx=")
3523  << idx << ")";
3524  }
3525  if (sourceVectorType.getScalableDims()[idx]) {
3526  auto sourceSize = sourceShape[idx];
3527  auto destSize = destShape[idx + rankDiff];
3528  if (sourceSize != destSize) {
3529  return emitOpError("expected size at idx=")
3530  << idx
3531  << (" to match the corresponding base size from the input "
3532  "vector (")
3533  << sourceSize << (" vs ") << destSize << (")");
3534  }
3535  }
3536  }
3537 
3538  return success();
3539 }
3540 
3541 namespace {
3542 /// Rewrite insert_strided_slice(splat-like(v), splat-like(v)) as v.
3543 class FoldInsertStridedSliceSplat final
3544  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3545 public:
3546  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3547 
3548  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp insertStridedSliceOp,
3549  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3550 
3551  auto dst = insertStridedSliceOp.getDest();
3552  auto splat = getScalarSplatSource(insertStridedSliceOp.getValueToStore());
3553  if (!splat || getScalarSplatSource(dst) != splat)
3554  return failure();
3555 
3556  rewriter.replaceOp(insertStridedSliceOp, dst);
3557  return success();
3558  }
3559 };
3560 
3561 /// Pattern to rewrite an InsertStridedSliceOp(ExtractStridedSliceOp(dst), dst)
3562 /// to dst.
3563 class FoldInsertStridedSliceOfExtract final
3564  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3565 public:
3566  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3567 
3568  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp insertStridedSliceOp,
3569  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3570  auto extractStridedSliceOp =
3571  insertStridedSliceOp.getValueToStore()
3572  .getDefiningOp<vector::ExtractStridedSliceOp>();
3573 
3574  if (!extractStridedSliceOp)
3575  return failure();
3576 
3577  if (extractStridedSliceOp.getOperand() != insertStridedSliceOp.getDest())
3578  return failure();
3579 
3580  // Check if have the same strides and offsets.
3581  if (extractStridedSliceOp.getStrides() !=
3582  insertStridedSliceOp.getStrides() ||
3583  extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets() != insertStridedSliceOp.getOffsets())
3584  return failure();
3585 
3586  rewriter.replaceOp(insertStridedSliceOp, insertStridedSliceOp.getDest());
3587  return success();
3588  }
3589 };
3590 
3591 // Pattern to rewrite an InsertStridedSliceOp(ConstantOp into ConstantOp) ->
3592 // ConstantOp.
3593 class InsertStridedSliceConstantFolder final
3594  : public OpRewritePattern<InsertStridedSliceOp> {
3595 public:
3596  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
3597 
3598  // Do not create constants with more than `vectorSizeFoldThreashold` elements,
3599  // unless the source vector constant has a single use.
3600  static constexpr int64_t vectorSizeFoldThreshold = 256;
3601 
3602  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(InsertStridedSliceOp op,
3603  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
3604  // Return if 'InsertOp' operand is not defined by a compatible vector
3605  // ConstantOp.
3606  TypedValue<VectorType> destVector = op.getDest();
3607  Attribute vectorDestCst;
3608  if (!matchPattern(destVector, m_Constant(&vectorDestCst)))
3609  return failure();
3610 
3611  VectorType destTy = destVector.getType();
3612  if (destTy.isScalable())
3613  return failure();
3614 
3615  // Make sure we do not create too many large constants.
3616  if (destTy.getNumElements() > vectorSizeFoldThreshold &&
3617  !destVector.hasOneUse())
3618  return failure();
3619 
3620  TypedValue<VectorType> sourceValue = op.getValueToStore();
3621  Attribute sourceCst;
3622  if (!matchPattern(sourceValue, m_Constant(&sourceCst)))
3623  return failure();
3624 
3625  // TODO: Support poison.
3626  if (isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(vectorDestCst) || isa<ub::PoisonAttr>(sourceCst))
3627  return failure();
3628 
3629  // TODO: Handle non-unit strides when they become available.
3630  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
3631  return failure();
3632 
3633  VectorType sliceVecTy = sourceValue.getType();
3634  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceShape = sliceVecTy.getShape();
3635  int64_t rankDifference = destTy.getRank() - sliceVecTy.getRank();
3636  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsets = getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets());
3637  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> destStrides = computeStrides(destTy.getShape());
3638 
3639  // Calcualte the destination element indices by enumerating all slice
3640  // positions within the destination and linearizing them. The enumeration
3641  // order is lexicographic which yields a sequence of monotonically
3642  // increasing linearized position indices.
3643  // Because the destination may have higher dimensionality then the slice,
3644  // we keep track of two overlapping sets of positions and offsets.
3645  auto denseDest = llvm::cast<DenseElementsAttr>(vectorDestCst);
3646  auto denseSlice = llvm::cast<DenseElementsAttr>(sourceCst);
3647  auto sliceValuesIt = denseSlice.value_begin<Attribute>();
3648  auto newValues = llvm::to_vector(denseDest.getValues<Attribute>());
3649  SmallVector<int64_t> currDestPosition(offsets.begin(), offsets.end());
3650  MutableArrayRef<int64_t> currSlicePosition(
3651  currDestPosition.begin() + rankDifference, currDestPosition.end());
3652  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceOffsets(offsets.begin() + rankDifference,
3653  offsets.end());
3654  do {
3655  int64_t linearizedPosition = linearize(currDestPosition, destStrides);
3656  assert(linearizedPosition < destTy.getNumElements() && "Invalid index");
3657  assert(sliceValuesIt != denseSlice.value_end<Attribute>() &&
3658  "Invalid slice element");
3659  newValues[linearizedPosition] = *sliceValuesIt;
3660  ++sliceValuesIt;
3661  } while (succeeded(
3662  incSlicePosition(currSlicePosition, sliceShape, sliceOffsets)));
3663 
3664  auto newAttr = DenseElementsAttr::get(destTy, newValues);
3665  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<arith::ConstantOp>(op, newAttr);
3666  return success();
3667  }
3668 };
3669 
3670 } // namespace
3671 
3672 void vector::InsertStridedSliceOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
3673  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
3674  results.add<FoldInsertStridedSliceSplat, FoldInsertStridedSliceOfExtract,
3675  InsertStridedSliceConstantFolder>(context);
3676 }

3678 OpFoldResult InsertStridedSliceOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
3679  if (getSourceVectorType() == getDestVectorType())
3680  return getValueToStore();
3681  return {};
3682 }

3690  Value lhs, Value rhs, Value acc) {

3695 void OuterProductOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
3696  p << " " << getLhs() << ", " << getRhs();
3697  if (getAcc()) {
3698  p << ", " << getAcc();
3699  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs());
3700  }
3701  p << " : " << getLhs().getType() << ", " << getRhs().getType();

3703 
3704 ParseResult OuterProductOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3705  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 3> operandsInfo;
3706  Type tLHS, tRHS;
3707  if (parser.parseOperandList(operandsInfo) ||
3708  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
3709  parser.parseColonType(tLHS) || parser.parseComma() ||
3710  parser.parseType(tRHS))
3711  return failure();
3712  if (operandsInfo.size() < 2)
3713  return parser.emitError(parser.getNameLoc(),
3714  "expected at least 2 operands");
3715  VectorType vLHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tLHS);
3716  VectorType vRHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tRHS);
3717  if (!vLHS)
3718  return parser.emitError(parser.getNameLoc(),
3719  "expected vector type for operand #1");
3720 
3721  VectorType resType;
3722  if (vRHS) {
3723  SmallVector<bool> scalableDimsRes{vLHS.getScalableDims()[0],
3724  vRHS.getScalableDims()[0]};
3725  resType = VectorType::get({vLHS.getDimSize(0), vRHS.getDimSize(0)},
3726  vLHS.getElementType(), scalableDimsRes);
3727  } else {
3728  // Scalar RHS operand
3729  SmallVector<bool> scalableDimsRes{vLHS.getScalableDims()[0]};
3730  resType = VectorType::get({vLHS.getDimSize(0)}, vLHS.getElementType(),
3731  scalableDimsRes);
3732  }
3733 
3734  if (!result.attributes.get(OuterProductOp::getKindAttrName(result.name))) {
3735  result.attributes.append(
3736  OuterProductOp::getKindAttrName(result.name),
3737  CombiningKindAttr::get(result.getContext(),
3738  OuterProductOp::getDefaultKind()));
3739  }
3740 
3741  return failure(
3742  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[0], tLHS, result.operands) ||
3743  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[1], tRHS, result.operands) ||
3744  (operandsInfo.size() > 2 &&
3745  parser.resolveOperand(operandsInfo[2], resType, result.operands)) ||
3746  parser.addTypeToList(resType, result.types));
3747 }
3748 
3749 LogicalResult OuterProductOp::verify() {
3750  Type tRHS = getOperandTypeRHS();
3751  VectorType vLHS = getOperandVectorTypeLHS(),
3752  vRHS = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(tRHS),
3753  vACC = getOperandVectorTypeACC(), vRES = getResultVectorType();
3754 
3755  if (vLHS.getRank() != 1)
3756  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector for operand #1");
3757 
3758  if (vRHS) {
3759  // Proper OUTER operation.
3760  if (vRHS.getRank() != 1)
3761  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector for operand #2");
3762  if (vRES.getRank() != 2)
3763  return emitOpError("expected 2-d vector result");
3764  if (vLHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(0))
3765  return emitOpError("expected #1 operand dim to match result dim #1");
3766  if (vRHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(1))
3767  return emitOpError("expected #2 operand dim to match result dim #2");
3768  if (vLHS.isScalable() && !vRHS.isScalable()) {
3769  // This restriction reflects what's currently supported in terms of
3770  // scalable vectors. However, we could relax this if there's a use case.
3771  return emitOpError(
3772  "expected either both or only #2 operand dim to be scalable");
3773  }
3774  } else {
3775  // An AXPY operation.
3776  if (vRES.getRank() != 1)
3777  return emitOpError("expected 1-d vector result");
3778  if (vLHS.getDimSize(0) != vRES.getDimSize(0))
3779  return emitOpError("expected #1 operand dim to match result dim #1");
3780  }
3781 
3782  if (vACC && vACC != vRES)
3783  return emitOpError("expected operand #3 of same type as result type");
3784 
3785  // Verify supported combining kind.
3786  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), vRES.getElementType()))
3787  return emitOpError("unsupported outerproduct type");
3788 
3789  return success();
3790 }
3791 
3792 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
3793 
3794 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
3795 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
3796 Type OuterProductOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
3797  auto vecType = this->getResultVectorType();
3798  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
3799  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
3800  vecType.getScalableDims());
3801 }
3802 
3803 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3804 // ExtractStridedSliceOp
3805 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3806 
3807 // Inference works as follows:
3808 // 1. Add 'sizes' from prefix of dims in 'offsets'.
3809 // 2. Add sizes from 'vectorType' for remaining dims.
3810 // Scalable flags are inherited from 'vectorType'.
3811 static Type inferStridedSliceOpResultType(VectorType vectorType,
3812  ArrayAttr offsets, ArrayAttr sizes,
3813  ArrayAttr strides) {
3814  assert(offsets.size() == sizes.size() && offsets.size() == strides.size());
3815  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> shape;
3816  shape.reserve(vectorType.getRank());
3817  unsigned idx = 0;
3818  for (unsigned e = offsets.size(); idx < e; ++idx)
3819  shape.push_back(llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(sizes[idx]).getInt());
3820  for (unsigned e = vectorType.getShape().size(); idx < e; ++idx)
3821  shape.push_back(vectorType.getShape()[idx]);
3822 
3823  return VectorType::get(shape, vectorType.getElementType(),
3824  vectorType.getScalableDims());
3825 }
3826 
3827 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
3828  Value source, ArrayRef<int64_t> offsets,
3829  ArrayRef<int64_t> sizes,
3830  ArrayRef<int64_t> strides) {
3831  result.addOperands(source);
3832  auto offsetsAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, offsets);
3833  auto sizesAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, sizes);
3834  auto stridesAttr = getVectorSubscriptAttr(builder, strides);
3835  result.addTypes(
3836  inferStridedSliceOpResultType(llvm::cast<VectorType>(source.getType()),
3837  offsetsAttr, sizesAttr, stridesAttr));
3838  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getOffsetsAttrName(result.name),
3839  offsetsAttr);
3840  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getSizesAttrName(result.name),
3841  sizesAttr);
3842  result.addAttribute(ExtractStridedSliceOp::getStridesAttrName(result.name),
3843  stridesAttr);
3844 }
3845 
3846 LogicalResult ExtractStridedSliceOp::verify() {
3847  auto type = getSourceVectorType();
3848  auto offsets = getOffsetsAttr();
3849  auto sizes = getSizesAttr();
3850  auto strides = getStridesAttr();
3851  if (offsets.size() != sizes.size() || offsets.size() != strides.size())
3852  return emitOpError(
3853  "expected offsets, sizes and strides attributes of same size");
3854 
3855  auto shape = type.getShape();
3856  auto offName = getOffsetsAttrName();
3857  auto sizesName = getSizesAttrName();
3858  auto stridesName = getStridesAttrName();
3859  if (failed(
3860  isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, offsets, shape, offName)) ||
3861  failed(
3862  isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, sizes, shape, sizesName)) ||
3863  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrSmallerThanShape(*this, strides, shape,
3864  stridesName)) ||
3865  failed(
3866  isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, shape, offName)) ||
3867  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, sizes, shape, sizesName,
3868  /*halfOpen=*/false,
3869  /*min=*/1)) ||
3870  failed(isIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToRange(*this, strides, /*min=*/1,
3871  /*max=*/1, stridesName,
3872  /*halfOpen=*/false)) ||
3873  failed(isSumOfIntegerArrayAttrConfinedToShape(*this, offsets, sizes,
3874  shape, offName, sizesName,
3875  /*halfOpen=*/false)))
3876  return failure();
3877 
3878  auto resultType = inferStridedSliceOpResultType(getSourceVectorType(),
3879  offsets, sizes, strides);
3880  if (getResult().getType() != resultType)
3881  return emitOpError("expected result type to be ") << resultType;
3882 
3883  for (unsigned idx = 0; idx < sizes.size(); ++idx) {
3884  if (type.getScalableDims()[idx]) {
3885  auto inputDim = type.getShape()[idx];
3886  auto inputSize = llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(sizes[idx]).getInt();
3887  if (inputDim != inputSize)
3888  return emitOpError("expected size at idx=")
3889  << idx
3890  << (" to match the corresponding base size from the input "
3891  "vector (")
3892  << inputSize << (" vs ") << inputDim << (")");
3893  }
3894  }
3895 
3896  return success();
3897 }
3898 
3899 // When the source of ExtractStrided comes from a chain of InsertStrided ops try
3900 // to use the source of the InsertStrided ops if we can detect that the
3901 // extracted vector is a subset of one of the vector inserted.
3902 static LogicalResult
3903 foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(ExtractStridedSliceOp op) {
3904  // Helper to extract integer out of ArrayAttr.
3905  auto getElement = [](ArrayAttr array, int idx) {
3906  return llvm::cast<IntegerAttr>(array[idx]).getInt();
3907  };
3908  ArrayAttr extractOffsets = op.getOffsets();
3909  ArrayAttr extractStrides = op.getStrides();
3910  ArrayAttr extractSizes = op.getSizes();
3911  auto insertOp = op.getVector().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
3912  while (insertOp) {
3913  if (op.getSourceVectorType().getRank() !=
3914  insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getRank())
3915  return failure();
3916  ArrayAttr insertOffsets = insertOp.getOffsets();
3917  ArrayAttr insertStrides = insertOp.getStrides();
3918  // If the rank of extract is greater than the rank of insert, we are likely
3919  // extracting a partial chunk of the vector inserted.
3920  if (extractOffsets.size() > insertOffsets.size())
3921  return failure();
3922  bool patialoverlap = false;
3923  bool disjoint = false;
3924  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsetDiffs;
3925  for (unsigned dim = 0, e = extractOffsets.size(); dim < e; ++dim) {
3926  if (getElement(extractStrides, dim) != getElement(insertStrides, dim))
3927  return failure();
3928  int64_t start = getElement(insertOffsets, dim);
3929  int64_t end = start + insertOp.getSourceVectorType().getDimSize(dim);
3930  int64_t offset = getElement(extractOffsets, dim);
3931  int64_t size = getElement(extractSizes, dim);
3932  // Check if the start of the extract offset is in the interval inserted.
3933  if (start <= offset && offset < end) {
3934  // If the extract interval overlaps but is not fully included we may
3935  // have a partial overlap that will prevent any folding.
3936  if (offset + size > end)
3937  patialoverlap = true;
3938  offsetDiffs.push_back(offset - start);
3939  continue;
3940  }
3941  disjoint = true;
3942  break;
3943  }
3944  // The extract element chunk is a subset of the insert element.
3945  if (!disjoint && !patialoverlap) {
3946  op.setOperand(insertOp.getValueToStore());
3947  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
3948  OpBuilder b(op.getContext());
3949  op.setOffsetsAttr(b.getI64ArrayAttr(offsetDiffs));
3950  return success();
3951  }
3952  // If the chunk extracted is disjoint from the chunk inserted, keep looking
3953  // in the insert chain.
3954  if (disjoint)
3955  insertOp = insertOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<InsertStridedSliceOp>();
3956  else {
3957  // The extracted vector partially overlap the inserted vector, we cannot
3958  // fold.
3959  return failure();
3960  }
3961  }
3962  return failure();
3963 }
3964 
3965 // ExtractStridedSliceOp(non-splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
3966 static OpFoldResult
3967 foldExtractStridedSliceNonSplatConstant(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
3968  Attribute foldInput) {
3969 
3970  auto dense = llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(foldInput);
3971  if (!dense)
3972  return {};
3973 
3974  // TODO: Handle non-unit strides when they become available.
3975  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
3976  return {};
3977 
3978  VectorType sourceVecTy = op.getSourceVectorType();
3979  ArrayRef<int64_t> sourceShape = sourceVecTy.getShape();
3980  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sourceStrides = computeStrides(sourceShape);
3981 
3982  VectorType sliceVecTy = op.getType();
3983  ArrayRef<int64_t> sliceShape = sliceVecTy.getShape();
3984  int64_t rank = sliceVecTy.getRank();
3985 
3986  // Expand offsets and sizes to match the vector rank.
3987  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsets(rank, 0);
3988  copy(getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets()), offsets.begin());
3989 
3990  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> sizes(sourceShape);
3991  copy(getI64SubArray(op.getSizes()), sizes.begin());
3992 
3993  // Calculate the slice elements by enumerating all slice positions and
3994  // linearizing them. The enumeration order is lexicographic which yields a
3995  // sequence of monotonically increasing linearized position indices.
3996  const auto denseValuesBegin = dense.value_begin<Attribute>();
3997  SmallVector<Attribute> sliceValues;
3998  sliceValues.reserve(sliceVecTy.getNumElements());
3999  SmallVector<int64_t> currSlicePosition(offsets.begin(), offsets.end());
4000  do {
4001  int64_t linearizedPosition = linearize(currSlicePosition, sourceStrides);
4002  assert(linearizedPosition < sourceVecTy.getNumElements() &&
4003  "Invalid index");
4004  sliceValues.push_back(*(denseValuesBegin + linearizedPosition));
4005  } while (succeeded(incSlicePosition(currSlicePosition, sliceShape, offsets)));
4006 
4007  assert(static_cast<int64_t>(sliceValues.size()) ==
4008  sliceVecTy.getNumElements() &&
4009  "Invalid number of slice elements");
4010  return DenseElementsAttr::get(sliceVecTy, sliceValues);
4011 }
4012 
4013 OpFoldResult ExtractStridedSliceOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
4014  if (getSourceVectorType() == getResult().getType())
4015  return getVector();
4016  if (succeeded(foldExtractStridedOpFromInsertChain(*this)))
4017  return getResult();
4018 
4019  // ExtractStridedSliceOp(splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4020  if (auto splat =
4021  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<SplatElementsAttr>(adaptor.getVector()))
4022  DenseElementsAttr::get(getType(), splat.getSplatValue<Attribute>());
4023 
4024  // ExtractStridedSliceOp(non-splat ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4025  return foldExtractStridedSliceNonSplatConstant(*this, adaptor.getVector());
4026 }

4028 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::getOffsets(SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &results) {
4029  populateFromInt64AttrArray(getOffsets(), results);
4030 }

4034 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(CreateMaskOp) to
4035 // CreateMaskOp.
4036 //
4037 // Example:
4038 //
4039 // %mask = vector.create_mask %ub : vector<16xi1>
4040 // %slice = vector.extract_strided_slice [%offset] [8] [1]
4041 //
4042 // to
4043 //
4044 // %new_ub = arith.subi %ub, %offset
4045 // %mask = vector.create_mask %new_ub : vector<8xi1>
4046 class StridedSliceCreateMaskFolder final
4047  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4048  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4049 
4050 public:
4051  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp extractStridedSliceOp,
4052  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4053  Location loc = extractStridedSliceOp.getLoc();
4054  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' operand is not defined by a
4055  // CreateMaskOp.
4056  auto createMaskOp =
4057  extractStridedSliceOp.getVector().getDefiningOp<CreateMaskOp>();
4058  if (!createMaskOp)
4059  return failure();
4060  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' has non-unit strides.
4061  if (extractStridedSliceOp.hasNonUnitStrides())
4062  return failure();
4063  // Gather constant mask dimension sizes.
4064  SmallVector<Value> maskDimSizes(createMaskOp.getOperands());
4065  // Gather strided slice offsets and sizes.
4066  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceOffsets;
4067  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets(),
4068  sliceOffsets);
4069  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceSizes;
4070  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getSizes(), sliceSizes);
4071 
4072  // Compute slice of vector mask region.
4073  SmallVector<Value> sliceMaskDimSizes;
4074  sliceMaskDimSizes.reserve(maskDimSizes.size());
4075  // sliceOffsets.size() <= maskDimSizes.size(), so we use llvm::zip and
4076  // only iterate on the leading dim sizes. The tail accounts for the
4077  // remaining dim sizes.
4078  for (auto [maskDimSize, sliceOffset, sliceSize] :
4079  llvm::zip(maskDimSizes, sliceOffsets, sliceSizes)) {
4080  // No need to clamp on min/max values, because create_mask has clamping
4081  // semantics, i.e. the sliceMaskDimSize is allowed to be negative or
4082  // greater than the vector dim size.
4083  IntegerAttr offsetAttr =
4084  rewriter.getIntegerAttr(maskDimSize.getType(), sliceOffset);
4085  Value offset = arith::ConstantOp::create(rewriter, loc, offsetAttr);
4086  Value sliceMaskDimSize =
4087  arith::SubIOp::create(rewriter, loc, maskDimSize, offset);
4088  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(sliceMaskDimSize);
4089  }
4090  // Add unchanged dimensions.
4091  llvm::append_range(
4092  sliceMaskDimSizes,
4093  llvm::drop_begin(maskDimSizes, sliceMaskDimSizes.size()));
4094  // Replace 'extractStridedSliceOp' with CreateMaskOp with sliced mask
4095  // region.
4096  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<CreateMaskOp>(
4097  extractStridedSliceOp, extractStridedSliceOp.getResult().getType(),
4098  sliceMaskDimSizes);
4099  return success();
4100  }
4101 };
4102 
4103 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantMaskOp) to
4104 // ConstantMaskOp.
4105 class StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder final
4106  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4107 public:
4108  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4109 
4110  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp extractStridedSliceOp,
4111  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4112  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' operand is not defined by a
4113  // ConstantMaskOp.
4114  auto *defOp = extractStridedSliceOp.getVector().getDefiningOp();
4115  auto constantMaskOp = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantMaskOp>(defOp);
4116  if (!constantMaskOp)
4117  return failure();
4118  // Return if 'extractStridedSliceOp' has non-unit strides.
4119  if (extractStridedSliceOp.hasNonUnitStrides())
4120  return failure();
4121  // Gather constant mask dimension sizes.
4122  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
4123  // Gather strided slice offsets and sizes.
4124  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceOffsets;
4125  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getOffsets(),
4126  sliceOffsets);
4127  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceSizes;
4128  populateFromInt64AttrArray(extractStridedSliceOp.getSizes(), sliceSizes);
4129 
4130  // Compute slice of vector mask region.
4131  SmallVector<int64_t> sliceMaskDimSizes;
4132  sliceMaskDimSizes.reserve(maskDimSizes.size());
4133  for (auto [maskDimSize, sliceOffset, sliceSize] :
4134  llvm::zip(maskDimSizes, sliceOffsets, sliceSizes)) {
4135  int64_t sliceMaskDimSize = std::max(
4136  static_cast<int64_t>(0),
4137  std::min(sliceOffset + sliceSize, maskDimSize) - sliceOffset);
4138  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(sliceMaskDimSize);
4139  }
4140  // Add unchanged dimensions.
4141  if (sliceMaskDimSizes.size() < maskDimSizes.size())
4142  for (size_t i = sliceMaskDimSizes.size(); i < maskDimSizes.size(); ++i)
4143  sliceMaskDimSizes.push_back(maskDimSizes[i]);
4144  // If any of 'sliceMaskDimSizes' are zero, then set all to zero (masked
4145  // region is a conjunction of mask dim intervals).
4146  if (llvm::is_contained(sliceMaskDimSizes, 0))
4147  sliceMaskDimSizes.assign(maskDimSizes.size(), 0);
4148 
4149  // Replace 'extractStridedSliceOp' with ConstantMaskOp with sliced mask
4150  // region.
4151  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<ConstantMaskOp>(
4152  extractStridedSliceOp, extractStridedSliceOp.getResult().getType(),
4153  sliceMaskDimSizes);
4154  return success();
4155  }
4156 };
4157 
4158 // Pattern to rewrite an ExtractStridedSliceOp(BroadcastOp) to
4159 // BroadcastOp(ExtractStrideSliceOp).
4160 class StridedSliceBroadcast final
4161  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4162 public:
4163  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4164 
4165  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4166  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4167  auto broadcast = op.getVector().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>();
4168  if (!broadcast)
4169  return failure();
4170  auto srcVecType =
4171  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcast.getSource().getType());
4172  unsigned srcRank = srcVecType ? srcVecType.getRank() : 0;
4173  auto dstVecType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(op.getType());
4174  unsigned dstRank = dstVecType.getRank();
4175  unsigned rankDiff = dstRank - srcRank;
4176  // Source dimensions can be broadcasted (1 -> n with n > 1) or sliced
4177  // (n -> m with n > m). If they are originally both broadcasted *and*
4178  // sliced, this can be simplified to just broadcasting.
4179  bool needsSlice = false;
4180  for (unsigned i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
4181  if (srcVecType.getDimSize(i) != 1 &&
4182  srcVecType.getDimSize(i) != dstVecType.getDimSize(i + rankDiff)) {
4183  needsSlice = true;
4184  break;
4185  }
4186  }
4187  Value source = broadcast.getSource();
4188  if (needsSlice) {
4189  SmallVector<int64_t> offsets =
4190  getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff);
4191  SmallVector<int64_t> sizes =
4192  getI64SubArray(op.getSizes(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff);
4193  for (unsigned i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
4194  if (srcVecType.getDimSize(i) == 1) {
4195  // In case this dimension was broadcasted *and* sliced, the offset
4196  // and size need to be updated now that there is no broadcast before
4197  // the slice.
4198  offsets[i] = 0;
4199  sizes[i] = 1;
4200  }
4201  }
4202  source = ExtractStridedSliceOp::create(
4203  rewriter, op->getLoc(), source, offsets, sizes,
4204  getI64SubArray(op.getStrides(), /*dropFront=*/rankDiff));
4205  }
4206  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(op, op.getType(), source);
4207  return success();
4208  }
4209 };
4210 
4211 /// Rewrite extract_strided_slice(splat-like(v)) with broadcast(v).
4212 class StridedSliceSplat final : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4213 public:
4214  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4215 
4216  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4217  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4218 
4219  Value splat = getScalarSplatSource(op.getVector());
4220  if (!splat)
4221  return failure();
4222  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(op, op.getType(), splat);
4223  return success();
4224  }
4225 };
4226 
4227 /// Pattern to rewrite simple cases of N-D extract_strided_slice, where the
4228 /// slice is contiguous, into extract and shape_cast.
4229 ///
4230 /// Example:
4231 /// Before:
4232 /// %1 = vector.extract_strided_slice %arg0 {
4233 /// offsets = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0],
4234 /// sizes = [1, 1, 1, 1, 8],
4235 /// strides = [1, 1, 1, 1, 1]
4236 /// } : vector<8x1x1x2x8xi8> to vector<1x1x1x1x8xi8>
4237 /// After:
4238 /// %0 = vector.extract %arg0[0, 0, 0, 0]
4239 /// : vector<8xi8> from vector<8x1x1x2x8xi8>
4240 /// %1 = vector.shape_cast %0
4241 /// : vector<8xi8> to vector<1x1x1x1x8xi8>
4242 ///
4243 class ContiguousExtractStridedSliceToExtract final
4244  : public OpRewritePattern<ExtractStridedSliceOp> {
4245 public:
4246  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4247 
4248  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ExtractStridedSliceOp op,
4249  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4250  if (op.hasNonUnitStrides())
4251  return failure();
4252  Value source = op.getOperand();
4253  auto sourceType = cast<VectorType>(source.getType());
4254  if (sourceType.isScalable() || sourceType.getRank() == 0)
4255  return failure();
4256 
4257  // Compute the number of offsets to pass to ExtractOp::build. That is the
4258  // difference between the source rank and the desired slice rank. We walk
4259  // the dimensions from innermost out, and stop when the next slice dimension
4260  // is not full-size.
4261  SmallVector<int64_t> sizes = getI64SubArray(op.getSizes());
4262  int numOffsets;
4263  for (numOffsets = sizes.size(); numOffsets > 0; --numOffsets) {
4264  if (sizes[numOffsets - 1] != sourceType.getDimSize(numOffsets - 1))
4265  break;
4266  }
4267 
4268  // If the created extract op would have no offsets, then this whole
4269  // extract_strided_slice is the identity and should have been handled by
4270  // other canonicalizations.
4271  if (numOffsets == 0)
4272  return failure();
4273 
4274  // If not even the inner-most dimension is full-size, this op can't be
4275  // rewritten as an ExtractOp.
4276  if (numOffsets == sourceType.getRank() &&
4277  static_cast<int>(sizes.size()) == sourceType.getRank())
4278  return failure();
4279 
4280  // The outer dimensions must have unit size.
4281  for (int i = 0; i < numOffsets; ++i) {
4282  if (sizes[i] != 1)
4283  return failure();
4284  }
4285 
4286  // Avoid generating slices that have leading unit dimensions. The shape_cast
4287  // op that we create below would take bad generic fallback patterns
4288  // (ShapeCastOpRewritePattern).
4289  while (numOffsets < static_cast<int>(sizes.size()) - 1 &&
4290  sizes[numOffsets] == 1) {
4291  ++numOffsets;
4292  }
4293 
4294  SmallVector<int64_t> offsets = getI64SubArray(op.getOffsets());
4295  auto extractOffsets = ArrayRef(offsets).take_front(numOffsets);
4296  Value extract = vector::ExtractOp::create(rewriter, op->getLoc(), source,
4297  extractOffsets);
4298  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(op, op.getType(), extract);
4299  return success();
4300  }
4301 };
4302 
4303 } // namespace
4304 
4305 void ExtractStridedSliceOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
4306  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
4307  // Pattern to rewrite a ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantMaskOp) ->
4308  // ConstantMaskOp and ExtractStridedSliceOp(ConstantOp) -> ConstantOp.
4309  results.add<StridedSliceCreateMaskFolder, StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder,
4310  StridedSliceBroadcast, StridedSliceSplat,
4311  ContiguousExtractStridedSliceToExtract>(context);
4312 }

4318 /// 1. Builder that sets padding to zero and an empty mask (variant with attrs).
4319 void TransferReadOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
4320  VectorType vectorType, Value source,
4321  ValueRange indices, std::optional<Value> padding,
4322  AffineMapAttr permutationMapAttr,
4323  /*optional*/ ArrayAttr inBoundsAttr) {
4324 
4325  Type elemType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()).getElementType();
4326  if (!padding)
4327  padding = ub::PoisonOp::create(builder, result.location, elemType);
4328  build(builder, result, vectorType, source, indices, permutationMapAttr,
4329  *padding, /*mask=*/Value(), inBoundsAttr);
4330 }

4340  ? builder.getBoolArrayAttr(inBounds.value())

4344  if (!padding)
4345  padding = ub::PoisonOp::create(builder, result.location, elemType);
4346  build(builder, result, vectorType, source, indices, *padding,
4347  permutationMapAttr, inBoundsAttr);

4370 template <typename EmitFun>
4371 static LogicalResult verifyPermutationMap(AffineMap permutationMap,
4372  EmitFun emitOpError) {
4373  SmallVector<bool, 8> seen(permutationMap.getNumInputs(), false);
4374  for (auto expr : permutationMap.getResults()) {
4375  auto dim = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(expr);
4376  auto zero = dyn_cast<AffineConstantExpr>(expr);
4377  if (zero) {
4378  if (zero.getValue() != 0) {
4379  return emitOpError(
4380  "requires a projected permutation_map (at most one dim or the zero "
4381  "constant can appear in each result)");
4382  }
4383  continue;
4384  }
4385  if (!dim) {
4386  return emitOpError("requires a projected permutation_map (at most one "
4387  "dim or the zero constant can appear in each result)");
4388  }
4389  if (seen[dim.getPosition()]) {
4390  return emitOpError(
4391  "requires a permutation_map that is a permutation (found one dim "
4392  "used more than once)");
4393  }
4394  seen[dim.getPosition()] = true;
4395  }
4396  return success();
4397 }
4398 
4399 static LogicalResult
4400 verifyTransferOp(VectorTransferOpInterface op, ShapedType shapedType,
4401  VectorType vectorType, VectorType maskType,
4402  VectorType inferredMaskType, AffineMap permutationMap,
4403  ArrayAttr inBounds) {
4404  if (op->hasAttr("masked")) {
4405  return op->emitOpError("masked attribute has been removed. "
4406  "Use in_bounds instead.");
4407  }
4408 
4409  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
4410  return op->emitOpError(
4411  "requires source to be a memref or ranked tensor type");
4412 
4413  auto elementType = shapedType.getElementType();
4414  DataLayout dataLayout = DataLayout::closest(op);
4415  if (auto vectorElementType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(elementType)) {
4416  // Memref or tensor has vector element type.
4417  unsigned sourceVecSize =
4418  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorElementType.getElementType()) *
4419  vectorElementType.getShape().back();
4420  unsigned resultVecSize =
4421  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorType.getElementType()) *
4422  vectorType.getShape().back();
4423  if (resultVecSize % sourceVecSize != 0)
4424  return op->emitOpError(
4425  "requires the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector to be an integral "
4426  "multiple of the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector of the source");
4427 
4428  unsigned sourceVecEltRank = vectorElementType.getRank();
4429  unsigned resultVecRank = vectorType.getRank();
4430  if (sourceVecEltRank > resultVecRank)
4431  return op->emitOpError(
4432  "requires source vector element and vector result ranks to match.");
4433  unsigned rankOffset = resultVecRank - sourceVecEltRank;
4434  // Check that permutation map results match 'rankOffset' of vector type.
4435  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != rankOffset)
4436  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with result dims of "
4437  "the same rank as the vector type");
4438 
4439  if (maskType)
4440  return op->emitOpError("does not support masks with vector element type");
4441  } else {
4442  // Memref or tensor has scalar element type.
4443  unsigned minorSize =
4444  vectorType.getRank() == 0 ? 1 : vectorType.getShape().back();
4445  unsigned resultVecSize =
4446  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(vectorType.getElementType()) * minorSize;
4447  if (resultVecSize % dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(elementType) != 0)
4448  return op->emitOpError(
4449  "requires the bitwidth of the minor 1-D vector to be an integral "
4450  "multiple of the bitwidth of the source element type");
4451 
4452  // Check that permutation map results match rank of vector type.
4453  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != vectorType.getRank())
4454  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with result dims of "
4455  "the same rank as the vector type");
4456  }
4457 
4458  if (permutationMap.getNumSymbols() != 0)
4459  return op->emitOpError("requires permutation_map without symbols");
4460 
4461  if (permutationMap.getNumInputs() != shapedType.getRank())
4462  return op->emitOpError("requires a permutation_map with input dims of the "
4463  "same rank as the source type");
4464 
4465  if (maskType && maskType != inferredMaskType)
4466  return op->emitOpError("inferred mask type (")
4467  << inferredMaskType << ") and mask operand type (" << maskType
4468  << ") don't match";
4469 
4470  if (permutationMap.getNumResults() != static_cast<int64_t>(inBounds.size()))
4471  return op->emitOpError("expects the in_bounds attr of same rank "
4472  "as permutation_map results: ")
4473  << AffineMapAttr::get(permutationMap)
4474  << " vs inBounds of size: " << inBounds.size();
4475 
4476  return success();
4477 }
4478 
4479 static void printTransferAttrs(OpAsmPrinter &p, VectorTransferOpInterface op) {
4480  SmallVector<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs;
4481  elidedAttrs.push_back(TransferReadOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr());
4482  if (op.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity())
4483  elidedAttrs.push_back(op.getPermutationMapAttrName());
4484  // Elide in_bounds attribute if all dims are out-of-bounds.
4485  if (llvm::none_of(op.getInBoundsValues(), [](bool b) { return b; }))
4486  elidedAttrs.push_back(op.getInBoundsAttrName());
4487  p.printOptionalAttrDict(op->getAttrs(), elidedAttrs);
4488 }

4490 void TransferReadOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
4491  p << " " << getBase() << "[" << getIndices() << "], " << getPadding();
4492  if (getMask())
4493  p << ", " << getMask();
4494  printTransferAttrs(p, *this);
4495  p << " : " << getShapedType() << ", " << getVectorType();
4496 }
4497 
4498 VectorType mlir::vector::inferTransferOpMaskType(VectorType vecType,
4499  AffineMap permMap) {
4500  auto i1Type = IntegerType::get(permMap.getContext(), 1);
4501  AffineMap invPermMap = inversePermutation(compressUnusedDims(permMap));
4502  assert(invPermMap && "Inversed permutation map couldn't be computed");
4503  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> maskShape = invPermMap.compose(vecType.getShape());
4504 
4505  // The MaskOp specification doesn't support 0-D vectors at the moment. Turn a
4506  // 0-D mask into a single-element 1-D mask.
4507  if (maskShape.empty())
4508  maskShape.push_back(1);
4509 
4510  SmallVector<bool> scalableDims =
4511  applyPermutationMap(invPermMap, vecType.getScalableDims());
4512 
4513  return VectorType::get(maskShape, i1Type, scalableDims);
4514 }
4515 
4516 ParseResult TransferReadOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
4517  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
4518  SMLoc typesLoc;
4519  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand sourceInfo;
4520  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 8> indexInfo;
4521  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand paddingInfo;
4522  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
4523  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand maskInfo;
4524  // Parsing with support for paddingValue.
4525  if (parser.parseOperand(sourceInfo) ||
4526  parser.parseOperandList(indexInfo, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Square) ||
4527  parser.parseComma() || parser.parseOperand(paddingInfo))
4528  return failure();
4529  ParseResult hasMask = parser.parseOptionalComma();
4530  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
4531  if (parser.parseOperand(maskInfo))
4532  return failure();
4533  }
4534  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
4535  parser.getCurrentLocation(&typesLoc) || parser.parseColonTypeList(types))
4536  return failure();
4537  if (types.size() != 2)
4538  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires two types");
4539  auto indexType = builder.getIndexType();
4540  auto shapedType = llvm::dyn_cast<ShapedType>(types[0]);
4541  if (!shapedType || !llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
4542  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires memref or ranked tensor type");
4543  VectorType vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(types[1]);
4544  if (!vectorType)
4545  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires vector type");
4546  auto permMapAttrName = TransferReadOp::getPermutationMapAttrName(result.name);
4547  Attribute permMapAttr = result.attributes.get(permMapAttrName);
4548  AffineMap permMap;
4549  if (!permMapAttr) {
4550  if (shapedType.getRank() <
4551  getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(shapedType, vectorType))
4552  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
4553  "expected a custom permutation_map when "
4554  "rank(source) != rank(destination)");
4555  permMap = getTransferMinorIdentityMap(shapedType, vectorType);
4556  result.attributes.set(permMapAttrName, AffineMapAttr::get(permMap));
4557  } else {
4558  permMap = llvm::cast<AffineMapAttr>(permMapAttr).getValue();
4559  }
4560  auto inBoundsAttrName = TransferReadOp::getInBoundsAttrName(result.name);
4561  Attribute inBoundsAttr = result.attributes.get(inBoundsAttrName);
4562  if (!inBoundsAttr) {
4563  result.addAttribute(inBoundsAttrName,
4564  builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
4565  SmallVector<bool>(permMap.getNumResults(), false)));
4566  }
4567  if (parser.resolveOperand(sourceInfo, shapedType, result.operands) ||
4568  parser.resolveOperands(indexInfo, indexType, result.operands) ||
4569  parser.resolveOperand(paddingInfo, shapedType.getElementType(),
4570  result.operands))
4571  return failure();
4572  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
4573  if (llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(shapedType.getElementType()))
4574  return parser.emitError(
4575  maskInfo.location, "does not support masks with vector element type");
4576  if (vectorType.getRank() != permMap.getNumResults()) {
4577  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
4578  "expected the same rank for the vector and the "
4579  "results of the permutation map");
4580  }
4581  // Instead of adding the mask type as an op type, compute it based on the
4582  // vector type and the permutation map (to keep the type signature small).
4583  auto maskType = inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permMap);
4584  if (parser.resolveOperand(maskInfo, maskType, result.operands))
4585  return failure();
4586  }
4587  result.addAttribute(TransferReadOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr(),
4588  builder.getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
4589  {1, static_cast<int32_t>(indexInfo.size()), 1,
4590  static_cast<int32_t>(hasMask.succeeded())}));
4591  return parser.addTypeToList(vectorType, result.types);
4592 }
4593 
4594 LogicalResult TransferReadOp::verify() {
4595  // Consistency of elemental types in source and vector.
4596  ShapedType shapedType = getShapedType();
4597  VectorType vectorType = getVectorType();
4598  VectorType maskType = getMaskType();
4599  auto paddingType = getPadding().getType();
4600  auto permutationMap = getPermutationMap();
4601  VectorType inferredMaskType =
4602  maskType ? inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permutationMap)
4603  : VectorType();
4604  auto sourceElementType = shapedType.getElementType();
4605 
4606  if (static_cast<int64_t>(getIndices().size()) != shapedType.getRank())
4607  return emitOpError("requires ") << shapedType.getRank() << " indices";
4608 
4609  if (failed(verifyTransferOp(cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(getOperation()),
4610  shapedType, vectorType, maskType,
4611  inferredMaskType, permutationMap, getInBounds())))
4612  return failure();
4613 
4614  if (auto sourceVectorElementType =
4615  llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(sourceElementType)) {
4616  // Source has vector element type.
4617  // Check that 'sourceVectorElementType' and 'paddingType' types match.
4618  if (sourceVectorElementType != paddingType)
4619  return emitOpError(
4620  "requires source element type and padding type to match.");
4621 
4622  } else {
4623  // Check that 'paddingType' is valid to store in a vector type.
4624  if (!VectorType::isValidElementType(paddingType))
4625  return emitOpError("requires valid padding vector elemental type");
4626 
4627  // Check that padding type and vector element types match.
4628  if (paddingType != sourceElementType)
4629  return emitOpError(
4630  "requires formal padding and source of the same elemental type");
4631  }
4632 
4633  return verifyPermutationMap(permutationMap,
4634  [&](Twine t) { return emitOpError(t); });
4635 }
4636 
4637 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
4638 
4639 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
4640 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
4641 Type TransferReadOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
4642  return inferTransferOpMaskType(getVectorType(), getPermutationMap());
4643 }

4648 VectorType TransferReadOp::getVectorType() {
4649  return cast<VectorType>(getVector().getType());
4650 }

4652 template <typename TransferOp>
4653 static bool isInBounds(TransferOp op, int64_t resultIdx, int64_t indicesIdx) {
4654  // TODO: support more aggressive createOrFold on:
4655  // op.getIndices()[indicesIdx] + vectorType < dim(op.getSource(), indicesIdx)
4656  if (op.getShapedType().isDynamicDim(indicesIdx))
4657  return false;
4658  Value index = op.getIndices()[indicesIdx];
4659  std::optional<int64_t> cstOp = getConstantIntValue(index);
4660  if (!cstOp.has_value())
4661  return false;
4662 
4663  int64_t sourceSize = op.getShapedType().getDimSize(indicesIdx);
4664  int64_t vectorSize = op.getVectorType().getDimSize(resultIdx);
4665 
4666  return cstOp.value() + vectorSize <= sourceSize;
4667 }
4668 
4669 template <typename TransferOp>
4670 static LogicalResult foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(TransferOp op) {
4671  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
4672  // TODO: Be less conservative.
4673  if (op.getTransferRank() == 0)
4674  return failure();
4675  AffineMap permutationMap = op.getPermutationMap();
4676  bool changed = false;
4677  SmallVector<bool, 4> newInBounds;
4678  newInBounds.reserve(op.getTransferRank());
4679  // Idxs of non-bcast dims - used when analysing bcast dims.
4680  SmallVector<unsigned> nonBcastDims;
4681 
4682  // 1. Process non-broadcast dims
4683  for (unsigned i = 0; i < op.getTransferRank(); ++i) {
4684  // 1.1. Already marked as in-bounds, nothing to see here.
4685  if (op.isDimInBounds(i)) {
4686  newInBounds.push_back(true);
4687  continue;
4688  }
4689  // 1.2. Currently out-of-bounds, check whether we can statically determine
4690  // it is inBounds.
4691  bool inBounds = false;
4692  auto dimExpr = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(permutationMap.getResult(i));
4693  if (dimExpr) {
4694  inBounds = isInBounds(op, /*resultIdx=*/i,
4695  /*indicesIdx=*/dimExpr.getPosition());
4696  nonBcastDims.push_back(i);
4697  }
4698 
4699  newInBounds.push_back(inBounds);
4700  // We commit the pattern if it is "more inbounds".
4701  changed |= inBounds;
4702  }
4703 
4704  // 2. Handle broadcast dims
4705  // If all non-broadcast dims are "in bounds", then all bcast dims should be
4706  // "in bounds" as well.
4707  bool allNonBcastDimsInBounds = llvm::all_of(
4708  nonBcastDims, [&newInBounds](unsigned idx) { return newInBounds[idx]; });
4709  if (allNonBcastDimsInBounds) {
4710  for (size_t idx : permutationMap.getBroadcastDims()) {
4711  changed |= !newInBounds[idx];
4712  newInBounds[idx] = true;
4713  }
4714  }
4715 
4716  if (!changed)
4717  return failure();
4718  // OpBuilder is only used as a helper to build an I64ArrayAttr.
4719  OpBuilder b(op.getContext());
4720  op.setInBoundsAttr(b.getBoolArrayAttr(newInBounds));
4721  return success();
4722 }
4723 
4724 template <typename TransferOp>
4725 static LogicalResult foldTransferFullMask(TransferOp op) {
4726  auto mask = op.getMask();
4727  if (!mask)
4728  return failure();
4729 
4730  if (getMaskFormat(mask) != MaskFormat::AllTrue)
4731  return failure();
4732 
4733  op.getMaskMutable().clear();
4734  return success();
4735 }
4736 
4737 /// ```
4738 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
4739 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
4740 /// %0 = vector.transfer_read %w0[%c1, %c0], %cf0 {in_bounds = [true, true]}
4741 /// : tensor<4x4xf32>, vector<1x4xf32>
4742 /// ```
4743 /// -> Folds into
4744 /// ```
4745 /// %v0
4746 /// ```
4747 static Value foldRAW(TransferReadOp readOp) {
4748  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(readOp.getShapedType()))
4749  return {};
4750  auto defWrite = readOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
4751  while (defWrite) {
4752  if (checkSameValueRAW(defWrite, readOp))
4753  return defWrite.getVector();
4754  if (!isDisjointTransferIndices(
4755  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(defWrite.getOperation()),
4756  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(readOp.getOperation())))
4757  break;
4758  defWrite = defWrite.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
4759  }
4760  return {};
4761 }
4762 
4763 OpFoldResult TransferReadOp::fold(FoldAdaptor) {
4764  if (Value vec = foldRAW(*this))
4765  return vec;
4766  /// transfer_read(memrefcast) -> transfer_read
4767  if (succeeded(foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(*this)))
4768  return getResult();
4769  if (succeeded(foldTransferFullMask(*this)))
4770  return getResult();
4771  if (succeeded(memref::foldMemRefCast(*this)))
4772  return getResult();
4773  if (succeeded(tensor::foldTensorCast(*this)))
4774  return getResult();
4775  return OpFoldResult();
4776 }

4796 namespace {
4797 /// Store to load forwarding for transfer operations with permuation maps.
4798 /// Even if the permutation maps are different we can still propagate the store
4799 /// into the load if the size of the dimensions read and written match. Then we
4800 /// can replace the transfer_read + transfer_write by vector.broadcast and
4801 /// vector.transpose.
4802 /// Example:
4803 /// ```
4804 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c0, %c0, %c0]
4805 /// {in_bounds = [true, true],
4806 /// permutation_map = affine_map<(d0, d1, d2) -> (d2, d1)>} :
4807 /// vector<4x1xf32>, tensor<4x4x4xf32>
4808 /// %r = vector.transfer_read %w0[%c0, %c0, %c0], %cf0
4809 /// {in_bounds = [true, true, true, true],
4810 /// permutation_map = affine_map<(d0, d1, d2) -> (d1, 0, d2, 0)>} :
4811 /// tensor<4x4x4xf32>, vector<1x100x4x5xf32>
4812 /// ```
4813 /// To:
4814 /// ```
4815 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %arg1 : vector<4x1xf32> to vector<100x5x4x1xf32>
4816 /// %r = vector.transpose %0, [3, 0, 2, 1] :
4817 /// vector<100x5x4x1xf32> to vector<1x100x4x5xf32>
4818 /// ```
4819 struct TransferReadAfterWriteToBroadcast
4820  : public OpRewritePattern<TransferReadOp> {
4821  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
4822 
4823  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransferReadOp readOp,
4824  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
4825  auto defWrite = readOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
4826  if (!defWrite)
4827  return failure();
4828  // Bail if we need an alias analysis.
4829  if (!readOp.hasPureTensorSemantics() || !defWrite.hasPureTensorSemantics())
4830  return failure();
4831  // Bail if we need a bounds analysis.
4832  if (readOp.hasOutOfBoundsDim() || defWrite.hasOutOfBoundsDim())
4833  return failure();
4834  // TODO: If the written transfer chunk is a superset of the read transfer
4835  // chunk we could do an extract_strided_slice.
4836  if (readOp.getTransferChunkAccessed() !=
4837  defWrite.getTransferChunkAccessed())
4838  return failure();
4839  // TODO: Support cases where a dim is explicitly written but implicitly
4840  // read (i.e., a unit dim that is rank reduced).
4841  if (getUnusedDimsBitVector({readOp.getPermutationMap()}) !=
4842  getUnusedDimsBitVector({defWrite.getPermutationMap()}))
4843  return failure();
4844  // This pattern should only catch the broadcast case, the non-broadcast case
4845  // should be done separately to keep application conditions clean and
4846  // separate.
4847  AffineMap readMap = compressUnusedDims(readOp.getPermutationMap());
4848  AffineMap writeMap = compressUnusedDims(defWrite.getPermutationMap());
4849  bool bcast = !readMap.getBroadcastDims().empty() ||
4850  !writeMap.getBroadcastDims().empty();
4851  if (!bcast)
4852  return failure();
4853  // At this point, we know we have a bcast.
4854  // Bail in the masked case (too complex atm and needed to properly account
4855  // for padding).
4856  if (readOp.getMask() || defWrite.getMask())
4857  return failure();
4858  // If indices are not the same a shift may be required, bail.
4859  if (readOp.getIndices() != defWrite.getIndices())
4860  return failure();
4861 
4862  Value vec = defWrite.getVector();
4863  // TODO: loop through the chain of transfer_write if we can prove that they
4864  // don't overlap with the transfer_read. This requires improving
4865  // `isDisjointTransferIndices` helper.
4866  AffineMap map = readMap.compose(writeMap);
4867  if (map.getNumResults() == 0)
4868  return failure();
4869  // Calculate the permutation to apply to go from the vector stored to the
4870  // vector read.
4871  SmallVector<unsigned> permutation;
4872  if (!map.isPermutationOfMinorIdentityWithBroadcasting(permutation))
4873  return failure();
4874 
4875  Location loc = readOp.getLoc();
4876  // Calculate the broadcast shape by applying the reverse permutation to the
4877  // final shape we want.
4878  ArrayRef<int64_t> destShape = readOp.getVectorType().getShape();
4879  SmallVector<int64_t> broadcastShape(destShape.size());
4880  SmallVector<bool> broadcastScalableFlags(destShape.size());
4881  for (const auto &pos : llvm::enumerate(permutation)) {
4882  broadcastShape[pos.value()] = destShape[pos.index()];
4883  broadcastScalableFlags[pos.value()] =
4884  readOp.getVectorType().getScalableDims()[pos.index()];
4885  }
4886  VectorType broadcastedType = VectorType::get(
4887  broadcastShape, defWrite.getVectorType().getElementType(),
4888  broadcastScalableFlags);
4889  vec = vector::BroadcastOp::create(rewriter, loc, broadcastedType, vec);
4890  SmallVector<int64_t> transposePerm(permutation.begin(), permutation.end());
4891  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::TransposeOp>(readOp, vec,
4892  transposePerm);
4893  return success();
4894  }
4895 };
4896 } // namespace
4897 
4898 void TransferReadOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
4899  MLIRContext *context) {
4900  results.add<TransferReadAfterWriteToBroadcast>(context);
4901 }

4954 ParseResult TransferWriteOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser,
4955  OperationState &result) {
4956  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
4957  SMLoc typesLoc;
4958  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand vectorInfo, sourceInfo;
4959  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 8> indexInfo;
4960  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
4961  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand maskInfo;
4962  if (parser.parseOperand(vectorInfo) || parser.parseComma() ||
4963  parser.parseOperand(sourceInfo) ||
4964  parser.parseOperandList(indexInfo, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Square))
4965  return failure();
4966  ParseResult hasMask = parser.parseOptionalComma();
4967  if (hasMask.succeeded() && parser.parseOperand(maskInfo))
4968  return failure();
4969  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
4970  parser.getCurrentLocation(&typesLoc) || parser.parseColonTypeList(types))
4971  return failure();
4972  if (types.size() != 2)
4973  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires two types");
4974  auto indexType = builder.getIndexType();
4975  VectorType vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(types[0]);
4976  if (!vectorType)
4977  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires vector type");
4978  ShapedType shapedType = llvm::dyn_cast<ShapedType>(types[1]);
4979  if (!shapedType || !llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(shapedType))
4980  return parser.emitError(typesLoc, "requires memref or ranked tensor type");
4981  auto permMapAttrName =
4982  TransferWriteOp::getPermutationMapAttrName(result.name);
4983  auto permMapAttr = result.attributes.get(permMapAttrName);
4984  AffineMap permMap;
4985  if (!permMapAttr) {
4986  if (shapedType.getRank() <
4987  getEffectiveVectorRankForXferOp(shapedType, vectorType))
4988  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
4989  "expected a custom permutation_map when "
4990  "rank(source) != rank(destination)");
4991  permMap = getTransferMinorIdentityMap(shapedType, vectorType);
4992  result.attributes.set(permMapAttrName, AffineMapAttr::get(permMap));
4993  } else {
4994  permMap = llvm::cast<AffineMapAttr>(permMapAttr).getValue();
4995  }
4996  auto inBoundsAttrName = TransferWriteOp::getInBoundsAttrName(result.name);
4997  Attribute inBoundsAttr = result.attributes.get(inBoundsAttrName);
4998  if (!inBoundsAttr) {
4999  result.addAttribute(inBoundsAttrName,
5000  builder.getBoolArrayAttr(
5001  SmallVector<bool>(permMap.getNumResults(), false)));
5002  }
5003  if (parser.resolveOperand(vectorInfo, vectorType, result.operands) ||
5004  parser.resolveOperand(sourceInfo, shapedType, result.operands) ||
5005  parser.resolveOperands(indexInfo, indexType, result.operands))
5006  return failure();
5007  if (hasMask.succeeded()) {
5008  if (llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(shapedType.getElementType()))
5009  return parser.emitError(
5010  maskInfo.location, "does not support masks with vector element type");
5011  if (vectorType.getRank() != permMap.getNumResults()) {
5012  return parser.emitError(typesLoc,
5013  "expected the same rank for the vector and the "
5014  "results of the permutation map");
5015  }
5016  auto maskType = inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permMap);
5017  if (parser.resolveOperand(maskInfo, maskType, result.operands))
5018  return failure();
5019  }
5020  result.addAttribute(TransferWriteOp::getOperandSegmentSizeAttr(),
5021  builder.getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
5022  {1, 1, static_cast<int32_t>(indexInfo.size()),
5023  static_cast<int32_t>(hasMask.succeeded())}));
5024  return failure(llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(shapedType) &&
5025  parser.addTypeToList(shapedType, result.types));
5026 }

5028 void TransferWriteOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
5029  p << " " << getVector() << ", " << getBase() << "[" << getIndices() << "]";
5030  if (getMask())
5031  p << ", " << getMask();
5032  printTransferAttrs(p, *this);
5033  p << " : " << getVectorType() << ", " << getShapedType();

5035 
5036 LogicalResult TransferWriteOp::verify() {
5037  // Consistency of elemental types in shape and vector.
5038  ShapedType shapedType = getShapedType();
5039  VectorType vectorType = getVectorType();
5040  VectorType maskType = getMaskType();
5041  auto permutationMap = getPermutationMap();
5042  VectorType inferredMaskType =
5043  maskType ? inferTransferOpMaskType(vectorType, permutationMap)
5044  : VectorType();
5045 
5046  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != shapedType.getRank())
5047  return emitOpError("requires ") << shapedType.getRank() << " indices";
5048 
5049  // We do not allow broadcast dimensions on TransferWriteOps for the moment,
5050  // as the semantics is unclear. This can be revisited later if necessary.
5051  if (hasBroadcastDim())
5052  return emitOpError("should not have broadcast dimensions");
5053 
5054  if (failed(verifyTransferOp(cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(getOperation()),
5055  shapedType, vectorType, maskType,
5056  inferredMaskType, permutationMap, getInBounds())))
5057  return failure();
5058 
5059  return verifyPermutationMap(permutationMap,
5060  [&](Twine t) { return emitOpError(t); });
5061 }
5062 
5063 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5064 // TransferWriteOp: MaskableOpInterface methods.
5065 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5066 
5067 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
5068 /// verification purposes.
5069 Type TransferWriteOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
5070  return inferTransferOpMaskType(getVectorType(), getPermutationMap());
5071 }
5072 
5073 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5074 // TransferWriteOp: VectorTransferOpInterface methods.
5075 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5076 Value TransferWriteOp::getVector() { return getOperand(0); }
5077 VectorType TransferWriteOp::getVectorType() {
5078  return cast<VectorType>(getValueToStore().getType());
5079 }

5081 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5082 // TransferWriteOp: fold methods.
5083 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5084 /// Fold:
5085 /// ```
5086 /// %t1 = ...
5087 /// %v = vector.transfer_read %t0[%c0...], {in_bounds = [true...]} :
5088 /// tensor<static_sizesxf32>, vector<static_sizesxf32>
5089 /// %t2 = vector.transfer_write %v, %t1[%c0...] {in_bounds = [true...]} :
5090 /// vector<static_sizesxf32>, tensor<static_sizesxf32>
5091 /// ```
5092 ///
5093 /// into:
5094 ///
5095 /// ```
5096 /// %t0
5097 /// ```
5098 ///
5099 /// The producer of t1 may or may not be DCE'd depending on whether it is a
5100 /// block argument or has side effects.
5101 static LogicalResult foldReadInitWrite(TransferWriteOp write,
5102  ArrayRef<Attribute>,
5103  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5104  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
5105  if (write.getTransferRank() == 0)
5106  return failure();
5107  auto rankedTensorType =
5108  llvm::dyn_cast<RankedTensorType>(write.getBase().getType());
5109  // If not operating on tensors, bail.
5110  if (!rankedTensorType)
5111  return failure();
5112  // If no read, bail.
5113  auto read = write.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferReadOp>();
5114  if (!read)
5115  return failure();
5116  // TODO: support 0-d corner case.
5117  if (read.getTransferRank() == 0)
5118  return failure();
5119  // For now, only accept minor identity. Future: composition is minor identity.
5120  if (!read.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity() ||
5121  !write.getPermutationMap().isMinorIdentity())
5122  return failure();
5123  // Bail on mismatching ranks.
5124  if (read.getTransferRank() != write.getTransferRank())
5125  return failure();
5126  // Bail on potential out-of-bounds accesses.
5127  if (read.hasOutOfBoundsDim() || write.hasOutOfBoundsDim())
5128  return failure();
5129  // Tensor types must be the same.
5130  if (read.getBase().getType() != rankedTensorType)
5131  return failure();
5132  // Vector types must be the same.
5133  if (read.getVectorType() != write.getVectorType())
5134  return failure();
5135  // Vector and Tensor shapes must match.
5136  if (read.getVectorType().getShape() != rankedTensorType.getShape())
5137  return failure();
5138  // If any index is nonzero.
5139  auto isNotConstantZero = [](Value v) {
5140  auto cstOp = getConstantIntValue(v);
5141  return !cstOp.has_value() || cstOp.value() != 0;
5142  };
5143  if (llvm::any_of(read.getIndices(), isNotConstantZero) ||
5144  llvm::any_of(write.getIndices(), isNotConstantZero))
5145  return failure();
5146  // Success.
5147  results.push_back(read.getBase());
5148  return success();
5149 }
5150 
5151 static bool checkSameValueWAR(vector::TransferReadOp read,
5152  vector::TransferWriteOp write) {
5153  return read.getBase() == write.getBase() &&
5154  read.getIndices() == write.getIndices() &&
5155  read.getPermutationMap() == write.getPermutationMap() &&
5156  read.getVectorType() == write.getVectorType() && !read.getMask() &&
5157  !write.getMask();
5158 }
5159 /// Fold transfer_write write after read:
5160 /// ```
5161 /// %t0 = ...
5162 /// %v = vector.transfer_read %t0[%c0...] :
5163 /// tensor<static_sizesxf32>, vector<static_sizesxf32>
5164 /// %t1 = vector.transfer_write %v, %t0[%c0...] :
5165 /// vector<static_sizesxf32>, tensor<static_sizesxf32>
5166 /// ```
5167 ///
5168 /// into:
5169 ///
5170 /// ```
5171 /// %t0
5172 /// ```
5173 static LogicalResult foldWAR(TransferWriteOp write,
5174  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5175  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(write.getBase().getType()))
5176  return failure();
5177  auto read = write.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferReadOp>();
5178  if (!read)
5179  return failure();
5180 
5181  if (!checkSameValueWAR(read, write))
5182  return failure();
5183  results.push_back(read.getBase());
5184  return success();
5185 }
5186 
5187 LogicalResult TransferWriteOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
5188  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
5189  if (succeeded(foldReadInitWrite(*this, adaptor.getOperands(), results)))
5190  return success();
5191  if (succeeded(foldWAR(*this, results)))
5192  return success();
5193  if (succeeded(foldTransferInBoundsAttribute(*this)))
5194  return success();
5195  if (succeeded(foldTransferFullMask(*this)))
5196  return success();
5197  return memref::foldMemRefCast(*this);
5198 }

5211  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Write::get(), &getBaseMutable(),
