5221 namespace {
5222 /// Remove dead transfer write from the SSA chain so that it an be eliminated by
5223 /// DCE
5224 /// ```
5225 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5226 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5227 /// %w1 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %w0[%c2, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5228 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5229 /// %w2 = vector.transfer_write %v1, %w1[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5230 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5231 /// ```
5232 ///
5233 /// into:
5234 ///
5235 /// ```
5236 /// %w0 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5237 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5238 /// %w1 = vector.transfer_write %v0, %arg0[%c2, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5239 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5240 /// %w2 = vector.transfer_write %v1, %w1[%c1, %c0] {in_bounds = [true, true]}
5241 /// : vector<1x4xf32>, tensor<4x4xf32>
5242 /// ```
5243 ///
5244 /// `%w0 = vector.transfer_write` op will be removed by DCE if it doesn't have
5245 /// any other uses.
5246 class FoldWaw final : public OpRewritePattern<TransferWriteOp> {
5247 public:
5248  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5249  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransferWriteOp writeOp,
5250  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5251  if (!llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(writeOp.getShapedType()))
5252  return failure();
5253  vector::TransferWriteOp writeToModify = writeOp;
5254 
5255  auto defWrite = writeOp.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
5256  while (defWrite) {
5257  if (checkSameValueWAW(writeOp, defWrite)) {
5258  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(writeToModify, [&]() {
5259  writeToModify.getBaseMutable().assign(defWrite.getBase());
5260  });
5261  return success();
5262  }
5263  if (!isDisjointTransferIndices(
5264  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(defWrite.getOperation()),
5265  cast<VectorTransferOpInterface>(writeOp.getOperation())))
5266  break;
5267  // If the previous write op doesn't have any other use we an safely look
5268  // at the previous store to see if it can be removed.
5269  if (!defWrite->hasOneUse())
5270  break;
5271  writeToModify = defWrite;
5272  defWrite = defWrite.getBase().getDefiningOp<vector::TransferWriteOp>();
5273  }
5274  return failure();
5275  }
5276 };
5277 
5278 /// Rewrite tensor::ExtractSliceOp(vector::TransferWriteOp) to
5279 /// vector::TransferWriteOp(tensor::ExtractSliceOp) if the full slice is
5280 /// overwritten and inserted into another tensor. After this rewrite, the
5281 /// operations bufferize in-place since all of them work on the same slice.
5282 ///
5283 /// For example:
5284 /// ```mlir
5285 /// %0 = vector.transfer_write %vec, %init_tensor[%c0, %c0]
5286 /// : vector<8x16xf32>, tensor<8x16xf32>
5287 /// %1 = tensor.extract_slice %0[0, 0] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5288 /// : tensor<8x16xf32> to tensor<?x?xf32>
5289 /// %r = tensor.insert_slice %1 into %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5290 /// : tensor<?x?xf32> into tensor<27x37xf32>
5291 /// ```
5292 /// folds to
5293 /// ```mlir
5294 /// %0 = tensor.extract_slice %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5295 /// : tensor<27x37xf32> to tensor<?x?xf32>
5296 /// %1 = vector.transfer_write %vec, %0[%c0, %c0]
5297 /// : vector<8x16xf32>, tensor<?x?xf32>
5298 /// %r = tensor.insert_slice %1 into %iter_arg[%iv0, %iv1] [%sz0, %sz1] [1, 1]
5299 /// : tensor<?x?xf32> into tensor<27x37xf32>
5300 /// ```
5301 struct SwapExtractSliceOfTransferWrite
5302  : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::InsertSliceOp> {
5303 public:
5304  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5305 
5306  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::InsertSliceOp insertOp,
5307  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5308  if (!insertOp.hasUnitStride())
5309  return failure();
5310  auto extractOp =
5311  insertOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<tensor::ExtractSliceOp>();
5312  if (!extractOp || !extractOp.hasUnitStride() || !extractOp->hasOneUse())
5313  return failure();
5314  auto transferOp = extractOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<TransferWriteOp>();
5315  if (!transferOp || !transferOp->hasOneUse())
5316  return failure();
5317 
5318  // Fail if vector::TransferWriteOp or tensor::ExtractSliceOp is
5319  // rank-reducing.
5320  if (insertOp.getSourceType().getRank() != transferOp.getTransferRank()) {
5321  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5322  "use-def chain is rank-reducing");
5323  }
5324 
5325  // Fail if tensor::ExtractSliceOp has non-zero offset.
5326  if (!extractOp.hasZeroOffset()) {
5327  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5328  "ExtractSliceOp has non-zero offset");
5329  }
5330 
5331  // Fail if tensor::TransferWriteOp has non-zero offset.
5332  if (!llvm::all_of(transferOp.getIndices(), [](Value value) {
5333  return getConstantIntValue(value) == static_cast<int64_t>(0);
5334  })) {
5335  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(insertOp,
5336  "TranferWriteOp has non-zero offset");
5337  }
5338 
5339  // Fail if tensor::ExtractSliceOp and tensor::InsertSliceOp sizes differ.
5340  if (insertOp.getMixedSizes().size() != extractOp.getMixedSizes().size()) {
5341  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5342  insertOp, "InsertSliceOp and ExtractSliceOp ranks differ");
5343  }
5344 
5345  for (auto [insertSize, extractSize] :
5346  llvm::zip_equal(insertOp.getMixedSizes(), extractOp.getMixedSizes())) {
5347  if (!isEqualConstantIntOrValue(insertSize, extractSize)) {
5348  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5349  insertOp, "InsertSliceOp and ExtractSliceOp sizes differ");
5350  }
5351  }
5352 
5353  // Fail if the vector::TransferWriteOp may not overwrite the full tensor.
5354  assert(transferOp.getVectorType().hasStaticShape() &&
5355  "expected vector to have a static shape");
5356  ArrayRef<int64_t> vectorShape = transferOp.getVectorType().getShape();
5357  SmallVector<int64_t> resultShape = applyPermutationMap(
5358  transferOp.getPermutationMap(), transferOp.getShapedType().getShape());
5359  if (transferOp.getMask() || !vectorShape.equals(resultShape)) {
5360  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
5361  insertOp, "TransferWriteOp may not write the full tensor.");
5362  }
5363 
5364  // Swap the tensor::ExtractSliceOp in front of the vector::TransferWriteOp.
5365  // Set all in_bounds to false and let the folder infer them.
5366  SmallVector<bool> newInBounds(vectorShape.size(), false);
5367  auto newExtractOp = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
5368  rewriter, extractOp.getLoc(), insertOp.getSourceType(),
5369  insertOp.getDest(), insertOp.getMixedOffsets(),
5370  insertOp.getMixedSizes(), insertOp.getMixedStrides());
5371  auto newTransferWriteOp = TransferWriteOp::create(
5372  rewriter, transferOp.getLoc(), transferOp.getVector(),
5373  newExtractOp.getResult(), transferOp.getIndices(),
5374  transferOp.getPermutationMapAttr(),
5375  rewriter.getBoolArrayAttr(newInBounds));
5376  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(insertOp, [&]() {
5377  insertOp.getSourceMutable().assign(newTransferWriteOp.getResult());
5378  });
5379  return success();
5380  }
5381 };
5382 
5383 } // namespace
5384 
5385 void TransferWriteOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
5386  MLIRContext *context) {
5387  results.add<FoldWaw, SwapExtractSliceOfTransferWrite>(context);
5388 }

5394 static LogicalResult verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(Operation *op,
5395  VectorType vecTy,
5396  MemRefType memRefTy) {
5397  // If rank==0 or size==1 it's equivalent to scalar load/store, so we don't
5398  // need any strides limitations.
5399  if (!vecTy.isScalable() &&
5400  (vecTy.getRank() == 0 || vecTy.getNumElements() == 1))
5401  return success();
5402 
5403  if (!memRefTy.isLastDimUnitStride())
5404  return op->emitOpError("most minor memref dim must have unit stride");
5405  return success();
5406 }
5407 
5408 LogicalResult vector::LoadOp::verify() {
5409  VectorType resVecTy = getVectorType();
5410  MemRefType memRefTy = getMemRefType();
5411 
5412  if (failed(verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(*this, resVecTy, memRefTy)))
5413  return failure();
5414 
5415  if (memRefTy.getRank() < resVecTy.getRank())
5416  return emitOpError(
5417  "destination memref has lower rank than the result vector");
5418 
5419  // Checks for vector memrefs.
5420  Type memElemTy = memRefTy.getElementType();
5421  if (auto memVecTy = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memElemTy)) {
5422  if (memVecTy != resVecTy)
5423  return emitOpError("base memref and result vector types should match");
5424  memElemTy = memVecTy.getElementType();
5425  }
5426 
5427  if (resVecTy.getElementType() != memElemTy)
5428  return emitOpError("base and result element types should match");
5429  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memRefTy.getRank())
5430  return emitOpError("requires ") << memRefTy.getRank() << " indices";
5431  return success();
5432 }
5433 
5434 OpFoldResult LoadOp::fold(FoldAdaptor) {
5435  if (succeeded(memref::foldMemRefCast(*this)))
5436  return getResult();
5437  return OpFoldResult();
5438 }

5442 }

5448 LogicalResult vector::StoreOp::verify() {
5449  VectorType valueVecTy = getVectorType();
5450  MemRefType memRefTy = getMemRefType();
5451 
5452  if (failed(verifyLoadStoreMemRefLayout(*this, valueVecTy, memRefTy)))
5453  return failure();
5454 
5455  if (memRefTy.getRank() < valueVecTy.getRank())
5456  return emitOpError("source memref has lower rank than the vector to store");
5457 
5458  // Checks for vector memrefs.
5459  Type memElemTy = memRefTy.getElementType();
5460  if (auto memVecTy = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memElemTy)) {
5461  if (memVecTy != valueVecTy)
5462  return emitOpError(
5463  "base memref and valueToStore vector types should match");
5464  memElemTy = memVecTy.getElementType();
5465  }
5466 
5467  if (valueVecTy.getElementType() != memElemTy)
5468  return emitOpError("base and valueToStore element type should match");
5469  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memRefTy.getRank())
5470  return emitOpError("requires ") << memRefTy.getRank() << " indices";
5471  return success();
5472 }

5487 LogicalResult MaskedLoadOp::verify() {
5488  VectorType maskVType = getMaskVectorType();
5489  VectorType passVType = getPassThruVectorType();
5490  VectorType resVType = getVectorType();
5491  MemRefType memType = getMemRefType();
5492 
5493  if (resVType.getElementType() != memType.getElementType())
5494  return emitOpError("base and result element type should match");
5495  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memType.getRank())
5496  return emitOpError("requires ") << memType.getRank() << " indices";
5497  if (resVType.getShape() != maskVType.getShape())
5498  return emitOpError("expected result shape to match mask shape");
5499  if (resVType != passVType)
5500  return emitOpError("expected pass_thru of same type as result type");
5501  return success();
5502 }

5504 namespace {
5505 class MaskedLoadFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<MaskedLoadOp> {
5506 public:
5507  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5508  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(MaskedLoadOp load,
5509  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5510  switch (getMaskFormat(load.getMask())) {
5511  case MaskFormat::AllTrue:
5512  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::LoadOp>(
5513  load, load.getType(), load.getBase(), load.getIndices());
5514  return success();
5515  case MaskFormat::AllFalse:
5516  rewriter.replaceOp(load, load.getPassThru());
5517  return success();
5518  case MaskFormat::Unknown:
5519  return failure();
5520  }
5521  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected 1DMaskFormat on MaskedLoad");
5522  }
5523 };

5564  store, store.getValueToStore(), store.getBase(), store.getIndices());
5565  return success();

5568  return success();

5570  return failure();

5573  }

5587 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

5589 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5590 
5591 LogicalResult GatherOp::verify() {
5592  VectorType indVType = getIndexVectorType();
5593  VectorType maskVType = getMaskVectorType();
5594  VectorType resVType = getVectorType();
5595  ShapedType baseType = getBaseType();
5596 
5597  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(baseType))
5598  return emitOpError("requires base to be a memref or ranked tensor type");
5599 
5600  if (resVType.getElementType() != baseType.getElementType())
5601  return emitOpError("base and result element type should match");
5602  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != baseType.getRank())
5603  return emitOpError("requires ") << baseType.getRank() << " indices";
5604  if (resVType.getShape() != indVType.getShape())
5605  return emitOpError("expected result dim to match indices dim");
5606  if (resVType.getShape() != maskVType.getShape())
5607  return emitOpError("expected result dim to match mask dim");
5608  if (resVType != getPassThruVectorType())
5609  return emitOpError("expected pass_thru of same type as result type");
5610  return success();
5611 }

5613 // MaskableOpInterface methods.
5614 
5615 /// Returns the mask type expected by this operation. Mostly used for
5616 /// verification purposes. It requires the operation to be vectorized."
5617 Type GatherOp::getExpectedMaskType() {
5618  auto vecType = this->getIndexVectorType();
5619  return VectorType::get(vecType.getShape(),
5620  IntegerType::get(vecType.getContext(), /*width=*/1),
5621  vecType.getScalableDims());
5622 }

5624 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> GatherOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
5625  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getVectorType().getShape());
5626 }
5627 
5628 /// Cheeck if `indexVec` is constant 1D vec of consecutive values [0, 1, 2, ...]
5629 static LogicalResult isZeroBasedContiguousSeq(Value indexVec) {
5630  auto vecType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(indexVec.getType());
5631  if (!vecType || vecType.getRank() != 1 || vecType.isScalable())
5632  return failure();
5633 
5634  if (indexVec.getDefiningOp<StepOp>())
5635  return success();
5636 
5637  DenseIntElementsAttr elements;
5638  if (!matchPattern(indexVec, m_Constant(&elements)))
5639  return failure();
5640 
5641  return success(
5642  llvm::equal(elements, llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, vecType.getNumElements())));
5643 }

5645 namespace {
5646 class GatherFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<GatherOp> {
5647 public:
5648  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5649  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(GatherOp gather,
5650  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5651  switch (getMaskFormat(gather.getMask())) {
5652  case MaskFormat::AllTrue:
5653  return failure(); // no unmasked equivalent
5654  case MaskFormat::AllFalse:
5655  rewriter.replaceOp(gather, gather.getPassThru());
5656  return success();
5657  case MaskFormat::Unknown:
5658  return failure();
5659  }
5660  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected 1DMaskFormat on GatherFolder");
5661  }
5662 };

5664 /// Fold gathers with consecutive offsets [0, 1, 2, ...] into contiguous
5665 /// maskedload. Only 1D fixed vectors are supported for now.
5666 class FoldContiguousGather final : public OpRewritePattern<GatherOp> {
5667 public:
5668  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5669  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(GatherOp op,
5670  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5671  if (!isa<MemRefType>(op.getBase().getType()))
5672  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(op, "base must be of memref type");
5673 
5674  if (failed(isZeroBasedContiguousSeq(op.getIndexVec())))
5675  return failure();
5676 
5677  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<MaskedLoadOp>(op, op.getType(), op.getBase(),
5678  op.getIndices(), op.getMask(),
5679  op.getPassThru());
5680  return success();
5681  }
5682 };
5683 } // namespace

5685 void GatherOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
5686  MLIRContext *context) {
5687  results.add<GatherFolder, FoldContiguousGather>(context);
5688 }

5691 // ScatterOp
5692 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5693 
5694 LogicalResult ScatterOp::verify() {
5695  VectorType indVType = getIndexVectorType();
5696  VectorType maskVType = getMaskVectorType();
5697  VectorType valueVType = getVectorType();
5698  MemRefType memType = getMemRefType();
5699 
5700  if (valueVType.getElementType() != memType.getElementType())
5701  return emitOpError("base and valueToStore element type should match");
5702  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memType.getRank())
5703  return emitOpError("requires ") << memType.getRank() << " indices";
5704  if (valueVType.getShape() != indVType.getShape())
5705  return emitOpError("expected valueToStore dim to match indices dim");
5706  if (valueVType.getShape() != maskVType.getShape())
5707  return emitOpError("expected valueToStore dim to match mask dim");
5708  return success();
5709 }

5722  return success();
5723  case MaskFormat::Unknown:
5724  return failure();

5756 LogicalResult ExpandLoadOp::verify() {
5757  VectorType maskVType = getMaskVectorType();
5758  VectorType passVType = getPassThruVectorType();
5759  VectorType resVType = getVectorType();
5760  MemRefType memType = getMemRefType();
5761 
5762  if (resVType.getElementType() != memType.getElementType())
5763  return emitOpError("base and result element type should match");
5764  if (llvm::size(getIndices()) != memType.getRank())
5765  return emitOpError("requires ") << memType.getRank() << " indices";
5766  if (resVType.getDimSize(0) != maskVType.getDimSize(0))
5767  return emitOpError("expected result dim to match mask dim");
5768  if (resVType != passVType)
5769  return emitOpError("expected pass_thru of same type as result type");
5770  return success();
5771 }

5854 
5855 LogicalResult ShapeCastOp::verify() {
5856 
5857  VectorType sourceType = getSourceVectorType();
5858  VectorType resultType = getResultVectorType();
5859 
5860  // Check that element type is preserved
5861  if (sourceType.getElementType() != resultType.getElementType())
5862  return emitOpError("has different source and result element types");
5863 
5864  // Check that number of elements is preserved
5865  int64_t sourceNElms = sourceType.getNumElements();
5866  int64_t resultNElms = resultType.getNumElements();
5867  if (sourceNElms != resultNElms) {
5868  return emitOpError() << "has different number of elements at source ("
5869  << sourceNElms << ") and result (" << resultNElms
5870  << ")";
5871  }
5872 
5873  // Check that (non-)scalability is preserved
5874  int64_t sourceNScalableDims = sourceType.getNumScalableDims();
5875  int64_t resultNScalableDims = resultType.getNumScalableDims();
5876  if (sourceNScalableDims != resultNScalableDims)
5877  return emitOpError() << "has different number of scalable dims at source ("
5878  << sourceNScalableDims << ") and result ("
5879  << resultNScalableDims << ")";
5880 
5881  return success();
5882 }
5883 
5884 /// Return true if `transpose` does not permute a pair of non-unit dims.
5885 /// By `order preserving` we mean that the flattened versions of the input and
5886 /// output vectors are (numerically) identical. In other words `transpose` is
5887 /// effectively a shape cast.
5888 static bool isOrderPreserving(TransposeOp transpose) {
5889  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpose.getPermutation();
5890  VectorType sourceType = transpose.getSourceVectorType();
5891  ArrayRef<int64_t> inShape = sourceType.getShape();
5892  ArrayRef<bool> inDimIsScalable = sourceType.getScalableDims();
5893  auto isNonScalableUnitDim = [&](int64_t dim) {
5894  return inShape[dim] == 1 && !inDimIsScalable[dim];
5895  };
5896  int64_t current = 0;
5897  for (auto p : permutation) {
5898  if (!isNonScalableUnitDim(p)) {
5899  if (p < current) {
5900  return false;
5901  }
5902  current = p;
5903  }
5904  }
5905  return true;
5906 }
5907 
5908 OpFoldResult ShapeCastOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
5909 
5910  VectorType resultType = getType();
5911 
5912  // No-op shape cast.
5913  if (getSource().getType() == resultType)
5914  return getSource();
5915 
5916  // shape_cast(shape_cast(x)) -> shape_cast(x)
5917  if (auto precedingShapeCast = getSource().getDefiningOp<ShapeCastOp>()) {
5918  setOperand(precedingShapeCast.getSource());
5919  return getResult();
5920  }
5921 
5922  // shape_cast(transpose(x)) -> shape_cast(x)
5923  if (auto transpose = getSource().getDefiningOp<TransposeOp>()) {
5924  if (isOrderPreserving(transpose)) {
5925  setOperand(transpose.getVector());
5926  return getResult();
5927  }
5928  return {};
5929  }
5930 
5931  // Y = shape_cast(broadcast(X))
5932  // -> X, if X and Y have same type
5933  if (auto bcastOp = getSource().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>()) {
5934  if (bcastOp.getSourceType() == resultType)
5935  return bcastOp.getSource();
5936  }
5937 
5938  // shape_cast(constant) -> constant
5939  if (auto denseAttr =
5940  dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
5941  return denseAttr.reshape(getType());
5942 
5943  // shape_cast(poison) -> poison
5944  if (llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<ub::PoisonAttr>(adaptor.getSource()))
5945  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
5946 
5947  return {};
5948 }
5949 
5950 namespace {
5951 
5952 /// Helper function that computes a new vector type based on the input vector
5953 /// type by removing the trailing one dims:
5954 ///
5955 /// vector<4x1x1xi1> --> vector<4x1xi1>
5956 ///
5957 static VectorType trimTrailingOneDims(VectorType oldType) {
5958  ArrayRef<int64_t> oldShape = oldType.getShape();
5959  ArrayRef<int64_t> newShape = oldShape;
5960 
5961  ArrayRef<bool> oldScalableDims = oldType.getScalableDims();
5962  ArrayRef<bool> newScalableDims = oldScalableDims;
5963 
5964  while (!newShape.empty() && newShape.back() == 1 && !newScalableDims.back()) {
5965  newShape = newShape.drop_back(1);
5966  newScalableDims = newScalableDims.drop_back(1);
5967  }
5968 
5969  // Make sure we have at least 1 dimension.
5970  // TODO: Add support for 0-D vectors.
5971  if (newShape.empty()) {
5972  newShape = oldShape.take_back();
5973  newScalableDims = oldScalableDims.take_back();
5974  }
5975 
5976  return VectorType::get(newShape, oldType.getElementType(), newScalableDims);
5977 }
5978 
5979 /// Folds qualifying shape_cast(create_mask) into a new create_mask
5980 ///
5981 /// Looks at `vector.shape_cast` Ops that simply "drop" the trailing unit
5982 /// dimension. If the input vector comes from `vector.create_mask` for which
5983 /// the corresponding mask input value is 1 (e.g. `%c1` below), then it is safe
5984 /// to fold shape_cast into create_mask.
5985 ///
5986 /// BEFORE:
5987 /// %1 = vector.create_mask %c1, %dim, %c1, %c1 : vector<1x[4]x1x1xi1>
5988 /// %2 = vector.shape_cast %1 : vector<1x[4]x1x1xi1> to vector<1x[4]xi1>
5989 /// AFTER:
5990 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c1, %dim : vector<1x[4]xi1>
5991 class ShapeCastCreateMaskFolderTrailingOneDim final
5992  : public OpRewritePattern<ShapeCastOp> {
5993 public:
5994  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
5995 
5996  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShapeCastOp shapeOp,
5997  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5998  Value shapeOpSrc = shapeOp->getOperand(0);
5999  auto createMaskOp = shapeOpSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>();
6000  auto constantMaskOp = shapeOpSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>();
6001  if (!createMaskOp && !constantMaskOp)
6002  return failure();
6003 
6004  VectorType shapeOpResTy = shapeOp.getResultVectorType();
6005  VectorType shapeOpSrcTy = shapeOp.getSourceVectorType();
6006 
6007  VectorType newVecType = trimTrailingOneDims(shapeOpSrcTy);
6008  if (newVecType != shapeOpResTy)
6009  return failure();
6010 
6011  auto numDimsToDrop =
6012  shapeOpSrcTy.getShape().size() - shapeOpResTy.getShape().size();
6013 
6014  // No unit dims to drop
6015  if (!numDimsToDrop)
6016  return failure();
6017 
6018  if (createMaskOp) {
6019  auto maskOperands = createMaskOp.getOperands();
6020  auto numMaskOperands = maskOperands.size();
6021 
6022  // Check every mask dim size to see whether it can be dropped
6023  for (size_t i = numMaskOperands - 1; i >= numMaskOperands - numDimsToDrop;
6024  --i) {
6025  auto constant = maskOperands[i].getDefiningOp<arith::ConstantIndexOp>();
6026  if (!constant || (constant.value() != 1))
6027  return failure();
6028  }
6029  SmallVector<Value> newMaskOperands =
6030  maskOperands.drop_back(numDimsToDrop);
6031 
6032  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>(shapeOp, shapeOpResTy,
6033  newMaskOperands);
6034  return success();
6035  }
6036 
6037  if (constantMaskOp) {
6038  auto maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
6039  auto numMaskOperands = maskDimSizes.size();
6040 
6041  // Check every mask dim size to see whether it can be dropped
6042  for (size_t i = numMaskOperands - 1; i >= numMaskOperands - numDimsToDrop;
6043  --i) {
6044  if (maskDimSizes[i] != 1)
6045  return failure();
6046  }
6047 
6048  auto newMaskOperands = maskDimSizes.drop_back(numDimsToDrop);
6049  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>(shapeOp, shapeOpResTy,
6050  newMaskOperands);
6051  return success();
6052  }
6053 
6054  return failure();
6055  }
6056 };
6057 
6058 /// Pattern to rewrite Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) as either
6059 /// i) Y = ShapeCast(X), or
6060 /// ii) Y = Broadcast(X)
6061 /// If both (i) and (ii) are possible, (i) is chosen.
6062 class ShapeCastBroadcastFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<ShapeCastOp> {
6063 public:
6064  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6065 
6066  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(ShapeCastOp shapeCastOp,
6067  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6068  auto broadcastOp =
6069  shapeCastOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<vector::BroadcastOp>();
6070  if (!broadcastOp)
6071  return failure();
6072 
6073  auto srcVectorType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcastOp.getSourceType());
6074  bool srcIsScalar = !srcVectorType;
6075 
6076  // Replace Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) with Y = ShapeCast(X).
6077  // Example:
6078  // %0 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3x4xf32> to vector<1x3x4xf32>
6079  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %0 : vector<1x3x4xf32> to vector<12xf32>
6080  // to
6081  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %in : vector<3x4xf32> to vector<12xf32>
6082  if (srcVectorType) {
6083  if (srcVectorType.getNumElements() ==
6084  shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType().getNumElements()) {
6085  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(
6086  shapeCastOp, shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType(),
6087  broadcastOp.getSource());
6088  return success();
6089  }
6090  }
6091 
6092  // Replace Y = ShapeCast(Broadcast(X)) with Y = Broadcast(X)
6093  // Example
6094  // %0 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3xf32> to vector<2x4x3xf32>
6095  // %1 = vector.shape_cast %0 : vector<2x4x3xf32> to vector<8x3xf32>
6096  // to
6097  // %1 = vector.broadcast %in : vector<3xf32> to vector<8x3xf32>
6098  VectorType dstVectorType = shapeCastOp.getResultVectorType();
6099  if (srcIsScalar || isBroadcastableTo(srcVectorType, dstVectorType) ==
6100  BroadcastableToResult::Success) {
6101  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(
6102  shapeCastOp, dstVectorType, broadcastOp.getSource());
6103  return success();
6104  }
6105  return failure();
6106  }
6107 };
6108 
6109 } // namespace
6110 
6111 void ShapeCastOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
6112  MLIRContext *context) {
6113  results
6114  .add<ShapeCastCreateMaskFolderTrailingOneDim, ShapeCastBroadcastFolder>(
6115  context);
6116 }

6118 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6119 // VectorBitCastOp
6120 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6121 
6122 LogicalResult BitCastOp::verify() {
6123  auto sourceVectorType = getSourceVectorType();
6124  auto resultVectorType = getResultVectorType();
6125 
6126  for (int64_t i = 0, e = sourceVectorType.getRank() - 1; i < e; i++) {
6127  if (sourceVectorType.getDimSize(i) != resultVectorType.getDimSize(i))
6128  return emitOpError("dimension size mismatch at: ") << i;
6129  }
6130 
6131  DataLayout dataLayout = DataLayout::closest(*this);
6132  auto sourceElementBits =
6133  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(sourceVectorType.getElementType());
6134  auto resultElementBits =
6135  dataLayout.getTypeSizeInBits(resultVectorType.getElementType());
6136 
6137  if (sourceVectorType.getRank() == 0) {
6138  if (sourceElementBits != resultElementBits)
6139  return emitOpError("source/result bitwidth of the 0-D vector element "
6140  "types must be equal");
6141  } else if (sourceElementBits * sourceVectorType.getShape().back() !=
6142  resultElementBits * resultVectorType.getShape().back()) {
6143  return emitOpError(
6144  "source/result bitwidth of the minor 1-D vectors must be equal");
6145  }
6146 
6147  return success();
6148 }
6149 
6150 OpFoldResult BitCastOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6151  // Nop cast.
6152  if (getSource().getType() == getResult().getType())
6153  return getSource();
6154 
6155  // Canceling bitcasts.
6156  if (auto otherOp = getSource().getDefiningOp<BitCastOp>()) {
6157  if (getResult().getType() == otherOp.getSource().getType())
6158  return otherOp.getSource();
6159 
6160  setOperand(otherOp.getSource());
6161  return getResult();
6162  }
6163 
6164  Attribute sourceConstant = adaptor.getSource();
6165  if (!sourceConstant)
6166  return {};
6167 
6168  Type srcElemType = getSourceVectorType().getElementType();
6169  Type dstElemType = getResultVectorType().getElementType();
6170 
6171  if (auto floatPack = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseFPElementsAttr>(sourceConstant)) {
6172  if (floatPack.isSplat()) {
6173  auto splat = floatPack.getSplatValue<FloatAttr>();
6174 
6175  // Casting fp16 into fp32.
6176  if (srcElemType.isF16() && dstElemType.isF32()) {
6177  uint32_t bits = static_cast<uint32_t>(
6178  splat.getValue().bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue());
6179  // Duplicate the 16-bit pattern.
6180  bits = (bits << 16) | (bits & 0xffff);
6181  APInt intBits(32, bits);
6182  APFloat floatBits(llvm::APFloat::IEEEsingle(), intBits);
6183  return DenseElementsAttr::get(getResultVectorType(), floatBits);
6184  }
6185  }
6186  }
6187 
6188  if (auto intPack = llvm::dyn_cast<DenseIntElementsAttr>(sourceConstant)) {
6189  if (intPack.isSplat()) {
6190  auto splat = intPack.getSplatValue<IntegerAttr>();
6191 
6192  if (llvm::isa<IntegerType>(dstElemType)) {
6193  uint64_t srcBitWidth = srcElemType.getIntOrFloatBitWidth();
6194  uint64_t dstBitWidth = dstElemType.getIntOrFloatBitWidth();
6195 
6196  // Casting to a larger integer bit width.
6197  if (dstBitWidth > srcBitWidth && dstBitWidth % srcBitWidth == 0) {
6198  APInt intBits = splat.getValue().zext(dstBitWidth);
6199 
6200  // Duplicate the lower width element.
6201  for (uint64_t i = 0; i < dstBitWidth / srcBitWidth - 1; i++)
6202  intBits = (intBits << srcBitWidth) | intBits;
6203  return DenseElementsAttr::get(getResultVectorType(), intBits);
6204  }
6205  }
6206  }
6207  }
6208 
6209  return {};
6210 }
6211 
6212 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6213 // TypeCastOp
6214 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6215 
6216 static SmallVector<int64_t, 8> extractShape(MemRefType memRefType) {
6217  auto vectorType = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(memRefType.getElementType());
6218  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> res(memRefType.getShape());
6219  if (vectorType)
6220  res.append(vectorType.getShape().begin(), vectorType.getShape().end());
6221  return res;
6222 }
6223 
6224 /// Build the canonical memRefType with a single vector.
6225 /// E.g. memref<4 x 5 x vector<6 x f32>> -> memref<vector<4 x 5 x 6 x f32>>.
6226 void TypeCastOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6227  Value source) {
6228  result.addOperands(source);
6229  MemRefType memRefType = llvm::cast<MemRefType>(source.getType());
6230  VectorType vectorType =
6231  VectorType::get(extractShape(memRefType),
6232  getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(memRefType)));
6233  result.addTypes(MemRefType::get({}, vectorType, MemRefLayoutAttrInterface(),
6234  memRefType.getMemorySpace()));
6235 }
6236 
6237 LogicalResult TypeCastOp::verify() {
6238  MemRefType canonicalType = getMemRefType().canonicalizeStridedLayout();
6239  if (!canonicalType.getLayout().isIdentity())
6240  return emitOpError("expects operand to be a memref with identity layout");
6241  if (!getResultMemRefType().getLayout().isIdentity())
6242  return emitOpError("expects result to be a memref with identity layout");
6243  if (getResultMemRefType().getMemorySpace() !=
6244  getMemRefType().getMemorySpace())
6245  return emitOpError("expects result in same memory space");
6246 
6247  auto sourceType = getMemRefType();
6248  auto resultType = getResultMemRefType();
6249  if (getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(sourceType)) !=
6250  getElementTypeOrSelf(getElementTypeOrSelf(resultType)))
6251  return emitOpError(
6252  "expects result and operand with same underlying scalar type: ")
6253  << resultType;
6254  if (extractShape(sourceType) != extractShape(resultType))
6255  return emitOpError(
6256  "expects concatenated result and operand shapes to be equal: ")
6257  << resultType;
6258  return success();
6259 }

6261 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6262 // TransposeOp
6263 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6264 
6265 void vector::TransposeOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6266  Value vector, ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation) {
6267  VectorType vt = llvm::cast<VectorType>(vector.getType());
6268  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> transposedShape(vt.getRank());
6269  SmallVector<bool, 4> transposedScalableDims(vt.getRank());
6270  for (unsigned i = 0; i < permutation.size(); ++i) {
6271  transposedShape[i] = vt.getShape()[permutation[i]];
6272  transposedScalableDims[i] = vt.getScalableDims()[permutation[i]];
6273  }
6274 
6275  result.addOperands(vector);
6276  result.addTypes(VectorType::get(transposedShape, vt.getElementType(),
6277  transposedScalableDims));
6278  result.addAttribute(TransposeOp::getPermutationAttrName(result.name),
6279  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(permutation));
6280 }
6281 
6282 OpFoldResult vector::TransposeOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6283  // Eliminate splat constant transpose ops.
6284  if (auto splat =
6285  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<SplatElementsAttr>(adaptor.getVector()))
6286  return splat.reshape(getResultVectorType());
6287 
6288  // Eliminate poison transpose ops.
6289  if (llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<ub::PoisonAttr>(adaptor.getVector()))
6290  return ub::PoisonAttr::get(getContext());
6291 
6292  // Eliminate identity transposes, and more generally any transposes that
6293  // preserves the shape without permuting elements.
6294  //
6295  // Examples of what to fold:
6296  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [0, 1] : vector<1x1xi8> to vector<1x1xi8>
6297  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [0, 1] : vector<2x2xi8> to vector<2x2xi8>
6298  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [1, 0] : vector<1x1xi8> to vector<1x1xi8>
6299  //
6300  // Example of what NOT to fold:
6301  // %0 = vector.transpose %arg, [1, 0] : vector<2x2xi8> to vector<2x2xi8>
6302  //
6303  if (getSourceVectorType() == getResultVectorType() &&
6304  isOrderPreserving(*this))
6305  return getVector();
6306 
6307  return {};
6308 }
6309 
6310 LogicalResult vector::TransposeOp::verify() {
6311  VectorType vectorType = getSourceVectorType();
6312  VectorType resultType = getResultVectorType();
6313  int64_t rank = resultType.getRank();
6314  if (vectorType.getRank() != rank)
6315  return emitOpError("vector result rank mismatch: ") << rank;
6316  // Verify transposition array.
6317  ArrayRef<int64_t> perm = getPermutation();
6318  int64_t size = perm.size();
6319  if (rank != size)
6320  return emitOpError("transposition length mismatch: ") << size;
6321  SmallVector<bool, 8> seen(rank, false);
6322  for (const auto &ta : llvm::enumerate(perm)) {
6323  if (ta.value() < 0 || ta.value() >= rank)
6324  return emitOpError("transposition index out of range: ") << ta.value();
6325  if (seen[ta.value()])
6326  return emitOpError("duplicate position index: ") << ta.value();
6327  seen[ta.value()] = true;
6328  if (resultType.getDimSize(ta.index()) != vectorType.getDimSize(ta.value()))
6329  return emitOpError("dimension size mismatch at: ") << ta.value();
6330  }
6331  return success();
6332 }
6333 
6334 std::optional<SmallVector<int64_t, 4>> TransposeOp::getShapeForUnroll() {
6335  return llvm::to_vector<4>(getResultVectorType().getShape());
6336 }
6337 
6338 void TransposeOp::inferResultRanges(ArrayRef<ConstantIntRanges> argRanges,
6339  SetIntRangeFn setResultRanges) {
6340  setResultRanges(getResult(), argRanges.front());
6341 }

6345 // Rewrites two back-to-back TransposeOp operations into a single TransposeOp.
6346 class TransposeFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp> {
6347 public:
6348  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6349 
6350  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(vector::TransposeOp transposeOp,
6351  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6352  // Composes two permutations: result[i] = permutation1[permutation2[i]].
6353  auto composePermutations = [](ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation1,
6354  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation2) {
6355  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> result;
6356  for (auto index : permutation2)
6357  result.push_back(permutation1[index]);
6358  return result;
6359  };
6360 
6361  // Return if the input of 'transposeOp' is not defined by another transpose.
6362  vector::TransposeOp parentTransposeOp =
6363  transposeOp.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::TransposeOp>();
6364  if (!parentTransposeOp)
6365  return failure();
6366 
6367  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> permutation = composePermutations(
6368  parentTransposeOp.getPermutation(), transposeOp.getPermutation());
6369  // Replace 'transposeOp' with a new transpose operation.
6370  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::TransposeOp>(
6371  transposeOp, transposeOp.getResult().getType(),
6372  parentTransposeOp.getVector(), permutation);
6373  return success();
6374  }
6375 };
6376 
6377 /// Replace transpose(splat-like(v)) with broadcast(v)
6378 class FoldTransposeSplat final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6379 public:
6380  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6381 
6382  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transposeOp,
6383  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6384  Value splat = getScalarSplatSource(transposeOp.getVector());
6385  if (!splat)
6386  return failure();
6387 
6388  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(
6389  transposeOp, transposeOp.getResultVectorType(), splat);
6390  return success();
6391  }
6392 };
6393 
6394 /// Folds transpose(create_mask) into a new transposed create_mask.
6395 class FoldTransposeCreateMask final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6396 public:
6397  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6398 
6399  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transpOp,
6400  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6401  Value transposeSrc = transpOp.getVector();
6402  auto createMaskOp = transposeSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>();
6403  auto constantMaskOp = transposeSrc.getDefiningOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>();
6404  if (!createMaskOp && !constantMaskOp)
6405  return failure();
6406 
6407  // Get the transpose permutation and apply it to the vector.create_mask or
6408  // vector.constant_mask operands.
6409  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpOp.getPermutation();
6410 
6411  if (createMaskOp) {
6412  auto maskOperands = createMaskOp.getOperands();
6413  SmallVector<Value> newOperands(maskOperands.begin(), maskOperands.end());
6414  applyPermutationToVector(newOperands, permutation);
6415 
6416  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::CreateMaskOp>(
6417  transpOp, transpOp.getResultVectorType(), newOperands);
6418  return success();
6419  }
6420 
6421  // ConstantMaskOp case.
6422  auto maskDimSizes = constantMaskOp.getMaskDimSizes();
6423  auto newMaskDimSizes = applyPermutation(maskDimSizes, permutation);
6424 
6425  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ConstantMaskOp>(
6426  transpOp, transpOp.getResultVectorType(), newMaskDimSizes);
6427  return success();
6428  }
6429 };
6430 
6431 /// Folds transpose(shape_cast) into a new shape_cast.
6432 class FoldTransposeShapeCast final : public OpRewritePattern<TransposeOp> {
6433 public:
6434  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6435 
6436  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TransposeOp transposeOp,
6437  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6438  auto shapeCastOp =
6439  transposeOp.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>();
6440  if (!shapeCastOp)
6441  return failure();
6442  if (!isOrderPreserving(transposeOp))
6443  return failure();
6444 
6445  VectorType resultType = transposeOp.getType();
6446 
6447  // We don't need to check isValidShapeCast at this point, because it is
6448  // guaranteed that merging the transpose into the the shape_cast is a valid
6449  // shape_cast, because the transpose just inserts/removes ones.
6450 
6451  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::ShapeCastOp>(transposeOp, resultType,
6452  shapeCastOp.getSource());
6453  return success();
6454  }
6455 };
6456 
6457 /// Folds transpose(broadcast(x)) to broadcast(x) if the transpose is
6458 /// 'order preserving', where 'order preserving' means the flattened
6459 /// inputs and outputs of the transpose have identical (numerical) values.
6460 ///
6461 /// Example:
6462 /// ```
6463 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %input : vector<1x1xi32> to vector<1x8xi32>
6464 /// %1 = vector.transpose %0, [1, 0] : vector<1x8xi32>
6465 /// to vector<8x1xi32>
6466 /// ```
6467 /// can be rewritten as the equivalent
6468 /// ```
6469 /// %0 = vector.broadcast %input : vector<1x1xi32> to vector<8x1xi32>.
6470 /// ```
6471 /// The algorithm works by partitioning dimensions into groups that can be
6472 /// locally permuted while preserving order, and checks that the transpose
6473 /// only permutes within these groups.
6474 ///
6475 /// Groups are either contiguous sequences of 1s, or non-1s (1-element groups).
6476 /// Consider broadcasting 4x1x1x7 to 2x3x4x5x6x7. This is equivalent to
6477 /// broadcasting from 1x1x4x1x1x7.
6478 /// ^^^ ^ ^^^ ^
6479 /// groups: 0 1 2 3
6480 /// Order preserving permutations for this example are ones that only permute
6481 /// within the groups [0,1] and [3,4], like (1 0 2 4 3 5 6).
6482 class FoldTransposeBroadcast : public OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp> {
6483 public:
6484  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6485  FoldTransposeBroadcast(MLIRContext *context, PatternBenefit benefit = 1)
6486  : OpRewritePattern<vector::TransposeOp>(context, benefit) {}
6487 
6488  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(vector::TransposeOp transpose,
6489  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6490 
6491  vector::BroadcastOp broadcast =
6492  transpose.getVector().getDefiningOp<vector::BroadcastOp>();
6493  if (!broadcast) {
6494  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(transpose,
6495  "not preceded by a broadcast");
6496  }
6497 
6498  auto inputType = dyn_cast<VectorType>(broadcast.getSourceType());
6499  VectorType outputType = transpose.getResultVectorType();
6500 
6501  // transpose(broadcast(scalar)) -> broadcast(scalar) is always valid
6502  bool inputIsScalar = !inputType;
6503  if (inputIsScalar) {
6504  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(transpose, outputType,
6505  broadcast.getSource());
6506  return success();
6507  }
6508 
6509  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutation = transpose.getPermutation();
6510  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
6511  int64_t inputRank = inputType.getRank();
6512  int64_t outputRank = transpose.getType().getRank();
6513  int64_t deltaRank = outputRank - inputRank;
6514 
6515  int low = 0;
6516  for (int inputIndex = 0; inputIndex < inputRank; ++inputIndex) {
6517  bool notOne = inputShape[inputIndex] != 1;
6518  bool prevNotOne = (inputIndex != 0 && inputShape[inputIndex - 1] != 1);
6519  bool groupEndFound = notOne || prevNotOne;
6520  if (groupEndFound) {
6521  int high = inputIndex + deltaRank;
6522  // Return failure if not all permutation destinations for indices in
6523  // [low, high) are in [low, high), i.e. the permutation is not local to
6524  // the group.
6525  for (int i = low; i < high; ++i) {
6526  if (permutation[i] < low || permutation[i] >= high) {
6527  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
6528  transpose, "permutation not local to group");
6529  }
6530  }
6531  low = high;
6532  }
6533  }
6534 
6535  // We don't need to check the final group [low, outputRank) because if it is
6536  // not locally bound, there must be a preceding group that already failed
6537  // the check (impossible to have just 1 non-locally bound group).
6538 
6539  // The preceding logic also ensures that at this point, the output of the
6540  // transpose is definitely broadcastable from the input shape, assert so:
6541  assert(vector::isBroadcastableTo(inputType, outputType) ==
6542  vector::BroadcastableToResult::Success &&
6543  "not broadcastable directly to transpose output");
6544 
6545  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<vector::BroadcastOp>(transpose, outputType,
6546  broadcast.getSource());
6547 
6548  return success();
6549  }
6550 };
6551 
6552 } // namespace
6553 
6554 void vector::TransposeOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(
6555  RewritePatternSet &results, MLIRContext *context) {
6556  results.add<FoldTransposeCreateMask, FoldTransposeShapeCast, TransposeFolder,
6557  FoldTransposeSplat, FoldTransposeBroadcast>(context);
6558 }

6564 void ConstantMaskOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
6565  VectorType type, ConstantMaskKind kind) {
6566  assert(kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllTrue ||
6567  kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllFalse);
6568  build(builder, result, type,
6569  kind == ConstantMaskKind::AllTrue
6570  ? type.getShape()
6571  : SmallVector<int64_t>(type.getRank(), 0));
6572 }
6573 
6574 LogicalResult ConstantMaskOp::verify() {
6575  auto resultType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType());
6576  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6577  if (resultType.getRank() == 0) {
6578  if (getMaskDimSizes().size() != 1)
6579  return emitError("array attr must have length 1 for 0-D vectors");
6580  auto dim = getMaskDimSizes()[0];
6581  if (dim != 0 && dim != 1)
6582  return emitError("mask dim size must be either 0 or 1 for 0-D vectors");
6583  return success();
6584  }
6585 
6586  // Verify that array attr size matches the rank of the vector result.
6587  if (static_cast<int64_t>(getMaskDimSizes().size()) != resultType.getRank())
6588  return emitOpError(
6589  "must specify array attr of size equal vector result rank");
6590  // Verify that each array attr element is in bounds of corresponding vector
6591  // result dimension size.
6592  auto resultShape = resultType.getShape();
6593  auto resultScalableDims = resultType.getScalableDims();
6594  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskDimSizes = getMaskDimSizes();
6595  for (const auto [index, maskDimSize] : llvm::enumerate(maskDimSizes)) {
6596  if (maskDimSize < 0 || maskDimSize > resultShape[index])
6597  return emitOpError(
6598  "array attr of size out of bounds of vector result dimension size");
6599  if (resultScalableDims[index] && maskDimSize != 0 &&
6600  maskDimSize != resultShape[index])
6601  return emitOpError(
6602  "only supports 'none set' or 'all set' scalable dimensions");
6603  }
6604  // Verify that if one mask dim size is zero, they all should be zero (because
6605  // the mask region is a conjunction of each mask dimension interval).
6606  bool anyZeros = llvm::is_contained(maskDimSizes, 0);
6607  bool allZeros = llvm::all_of(maskDimSizes, [](int64_t s) { return s == 0; });
6608  if (anyZeros && !allZeros)
6609  return emitOpError("expected all mask dim sizes to be zeros, "
6610  "as a result of conjunction with zero mask dim");
6611  return success();
6612 }
6613 
6614 bool ConstantMaskOp::isAllOnesMask() {
6615  auto resultType = getVectorType();
6616  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6617  if (resultType.getRank() == 0) {
6618  assert(getMaskDimSizes().size() == 1 && "invalid sizes for zero rank mask");
6619  return getMaskDimSizes()[0] == 1;
6620  }
6621  for (const auto [resultSize, maskDimSize] :
6622  llvm::zip_equal(resultType.getShape(), getMaskDimSizes())) {
6623  if (maskDimSize < resultSize)
6624  return false;
6625  }
6626  return true;
6627 }
6628 
6629 OpFoldResult ConstantMaskOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
6630  ArrayRef<int64_t> bounds = getMaskDimSizes();
6631  ArrayRef<int64_t> vectorSizes = getVectorType().getShape();
6632 
6633  auto createBoolSplat = [&](bool x) {
6634  return SplatElementsAttr::get(getVectorType(),
6635  BoolAttr::get(getContext(), x));
6636  };
6637 
6638  // Check the corner case of 0-D vectors first.
6639  if (vectorSizes.empty()) {
6640  assert(bounds.size() == 1 && "invalid sizes for zero rank mask");
6641  return createBoolSplat(bounds[0] == 1);
6642  }
6643  // Fold vector.constant_mask to splat if possible.
6644  if (bounds == vectorSizes)
6645  return createBoolSplat(true);
6646  if (llvm::all_of(bounds, [](int64_t x) { return x == 0; }))
6647  return createBoolSplat(false);
6648  return OpFoldResult();
6649 }

6655 void CreateMaskOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,

6659  getValueOrCreateConstantIndexOp(builder, result.location, mixedOperands);

6663 LogicalResult CreateMaskOp::verify() {
6664  auto vectorType = llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType());
6665  // Verify that an operand was specified for each result vector each dimension.
6666  if (vectorType.getRank() == 0) {
6667  if (getNumOperands() != 1)
6668  return emitOpError(
6669  "must specify exactly one operand for 0-D create_mask");
6670  } else if (getNumOperands() !=
6671  llvm::cast<VectorType>(getResult().getType()).getRank()) {
6672  return emitOpError(
6673  "must specify an operand for each result vector dimension");
6674  }
6675  return success();
6676 }

6678 namespace {
6679 
6680 /// Pattern to rewrite a CreateMaskOp with a ConstantMaskOp.
6681 ///
6682 /// Ex 1:
6683 /// %c2 = arith.constant 2 : index
6684 /// %c3 = arith.constant 3 : index
6685 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c3, %c2 : vector<4x3xi1>
6686 /// Becomes:
6687 /// vector.constant_mask [3, 2] : vector<4x3xi1>
6688 ///
6689 /// Ex 2:
6690 /// %c_neg_1 = arith.constant -1 : index
6691 /// %0 = vector.create_mask %c_neg_1 : vector<[8]xi1>
6692 /// becomes:
6693 /// vector.constant_mask [0] : vector<[8]xi1>
6694 ///
6695 /// Ex 3:
6696 /// %c8 = arith.constant 8 : index
6697 /// %c16 = arith.constant 16 : index
6698 /// %0 = vector.vscale
6699 /// %1 = arith.muli %0, %c16 : index
6700 /// %10 = vector.create_mask %c8, %1 : vector<8x[16]xi1>
6701 /// becomes:
6702 /// %0 = vector.constant_mask [8, 16] : vector<8x[16]xi1>
6703 class CreateMaskFolder final : public OpRewritePattern<CreateMaskOp> {
6704 public:
6705  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
6706 
6707  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(CreateMaskOp createMaskOp,
6708  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
6709  VectorType maskType = createMaskOp.getVectorType();
6710  ArrayRef<int64_t> maskTypeDimSizes = maskType.getShape();
6711  ArrayRef<bool> maskTypeDimScalableFlags = maskType.getScalableDims();
6712 
6713  // Special case: Rank zero shape.
6714  constexpr std::array<int64_t, 1> rankZeroShape{1};
6715  constexpr std::array<bool, 1> rankZeroScalableDims{false};
6716  if (maskType.getRank() == 0) {
6717  maskTypeDimSizes = rankZeroShape;
6718  maskTypeDimScalableFlags = rankZeroScalableDims;
6719  }
6720 
6721  // Determine if this CreateMaskOp can be folded to a ConstantMaskOp and
6722  // collect the `constantDims` (for the ConstantMaskOp).
6723  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> constantDims;
6724  for (auto [i, dimSize] : llvm::enumerate(createMaskOp.getOperands())) {
6725  if (auto intSize = getConstantIntValue(dimSize)) {
6726  // Constant value.
6727  // If the mask dim is non-scalable this can be any value.
6728  // If the mask dim is scalable only zero (all-false) is supported.
6729  if (maskTypeDimScalableFlags[i] && intSize >= 0)
6730  return failure();
6731  constantDims.push_back(*intSize);
6732  } else if (auto vscaleMultiplier = getConstantVscaleMultiplier(dimSize)) {
6733  // Constant vscale multiple (e.g. 4 x vscale).
6734  // Must be all-true to fold to a ConstantMask.
6735  if (vscaleMultiplier < maskTypeDimSizes[i])
6736  return failure();
6737  constantDims.push_back(*vscaleMultiplier);
6738  } else {
6739  return failure();
6740  }
6741  }
6742 
6743  // Clamp values to constant_mask bounds.
6744  for (auto [value, maskDimSize] : llvm::zip(constantDims, maskTypeDimSizes))
6745  value = std::clamp<int64_t>(value, 0, maskDimSize);
6746 
6747  // If one of dim sizes is zero, set all dims to zero.
6748  if (llvm::is_contained(constantDims, 0))
6749  constantDims.assign(constantDims.size(), 0);
6750 
6751  // Replace 'createMaskOp' with ConstantMaskOp.
6752  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<ConstantMaskOp>(createMaskOp, maskType,
6753  constantDims);
6754  return success();
6755  }
6756 };
6757 
6758 } // namespace
6759 
6760 void CreateMaskOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
6761  MLIRContext *context) {
6762  results.add<CreateMaskFolder>(context);
6763 }

6769 void MaskOp::build(
6770  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, Value mask,
6771  Operation *maskableOp,
6772  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Operation *)> maskRegionBuilder) {
6773  assert(maskRegionBuilder &&
6774  "builder callback for 'maskRegion' must be present");
6775 
6776  result.addOperands(mask);
6777  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(builder);
6778  Region *maskRegion = result.addRegion();
6779  builder.createBlock(maskRegion);
6780  maskRegionBuilder(builder, maskableOp);
6781 }

6785  Value mask, Operation *maskableOp,
6786  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Operation *)> maskRegionBuilder) {
6787  build(builder, result, resultTypes, mask, /*passthru=*/Value(), maskableOp,
6788  maskRegionBuilder);

6791 void MaskOp::build(
6792  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, TypeRange resultTypes,
6793  Value mask, Value passthru, Operation *maskableOp,
6794  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Operation *)> maskRegionBuilder) {
6795  build(builder, result, mask, maskableOp, maskRegionBuilder);
6796  if (passthru)
6797  result.addOperands(passthru);
6798  result.addTypes(resultTypes);

6800 
6801 ParseResult MaskOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
6802  // Create the op region.
6803  result.regions.reserve(1);
6804  Region &maskRegion = *result.addRegion();
6805 
6806  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
6807 
6808  // Parse all the operands.
6809  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand mask;
6810  if (parser.parseOperand(mask))
6811  return failure();
6812 
6813  // Optional passthru operand.
6814  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand passthru;
6815  ParseResult parsePassthru = parser.parseOptionalComma();
6816  if (parsePassthru.succeeded() && parser.parseOperand(passthru))
6817  return failure();
6818 
6819  // Parse op region.
6820  if (parser.parseRegion(maskRegion, /*arguments=*/{}, /*argTypes=*/{}))
6821  return failure();
6822 
6823  MaskOp::ensureTerminator(maskRegion, builder, result.location);
6824 
6825  // Parse the optional attribute list.
6826  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
6827  return failure();
6828 
6829  // Parse all the types.
6830  Type maskType;
6831  if (parser.parseColonType(maskType))
6832  return failure();
6833 
6834  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
6835  if (parser.parseOptionalArrowTypeList(resultTypes))
6836  return failure();
6837  result.types.append(resultTypes);
6838 
6839  // Resolve operands.
6840  if (parser.resolveOperand(mask, maskType, result.operands))
6841  return failure();
6842 
6843  if (parsePassthru.succeeded()) {
6844  if (resultTypes.empty())
6845  return parser.emitError(
6846  parser.getNameLoc(),
6847  "expects a result if passthru operand is provided");
6848 
6849  if (parser.resolveOperand(passthru, resultTypes[0], result.operands))
6850  return failure();
6851  }
6852 
6853  return success();
6854 }
6855 
6856 void mlir::vector::MaskOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
6857  p << " " << getMask();
6858  if (getPassthru())
6859  p << ", " << getPassthru();
6860 
6861  // Print single masked operation and skip terminator.
6862  p << " { ";
6863  Block *singleBlock = &getMaskRegion().getBlocks().front();
6864  if (singleBlock && !singleBlock->getOperations().empty())
6865  p.printCustomOrGenericOp(&singleBlock->front());
6866  p << " }";
6867 
6868  p.printOptionalAttrDict(getOperation()->getAttrs());
6869 
6870  p << " : " << getMask().getType();
6871  if (getNumResults() > 0)
6872  p << " -> " << getResultTypes();
6873 }
6874 
6875 void MaskOp::ensureTerminator(Region &region, Builder &builder, Location loc) {
6876  // 1. For an empty `vector.mask`, create a default terminator.
6877  if (region.empty() || region.front().empty()) {
6878  OpTrait::SingleBlockImplicitTerminator<vector::YieldOp>::Impl<
6879  MaskOp>::ensureTerminator(region, builder, loc);
6880  return;
6881  }
6882 
6883  // 2. For a non-empty `vector.mask` with an explicit terminator, do nothing.
6884  Block &block = region.front();
6885  if (isa<vector::YieldOp>(block.back()))
6886  return;
6887 
6888  // 3. For a non-empty `vector.mask` without an explicit terminator:
6889 
6890  // Create default terminator if the number of masked operations is not
6891  // one. This case will trigger a verification failure.
6892  if (block.getOperations().size() != 1) {
6893  OpTrait::SingleBlockImplicitTerminator<vector::YieldOp>::Impl<
6894  MaskOp>::ensureTerminator(region, builder, loc);
6895  return;
6896  }
6897 
6898  // Create a terminator that yields the results from the masked operation.
6899  OpBuilder opBuilder(builder.getContext());
6900  Operation *maskedOp = &block.front();
6901  opBuilder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
6902  vector::YieldOp::create(opBuilder, loc, maskedOp->getResults());
6903 }
6904 
6905 LogicalResult MaskOp::verify() {
6906  // Structural checks.
6907  Block &block = getMaskRegion().getBlocks().front();
6908  if (block.getOperations().empty())
6909  return emitOpError("expects a terminator within the mask region");
6910 
6911  unsigned numMaskRegionOps = block.getOperations().size();
6912  if (numMaskRegionOps > 2)
6913  return emitOpError("expects only one operation to mask");
6914 
6915  // Terminator checks.
6916  auto terminator = dyn_cast<vector::YieldOp>(block.back());
6917  if (!terminator)
6918  return emitOpError("expects a terminator within the mask region");
6919 
6920  if (terminator->getNumOperands() != getNumResults())
6921  return emitOpError(
6922  "expects number of results to match mask region yielded values");
6923 
6924  // Empty vector.mask. Nothing else to check.
6925  if (numMaskRegionOps == 1)
6926  return success();
6927 
6928  auto maskableOp = dyn_cast<MaskableOpInterface>(block.front());
6929  if (!maskableOp)
6930  return emitOpError("expects a MaskableOpInterface within the mask region");
6931 
6932  // Result checks.
6933  if (maskableOp->getNumResults() != getNumResults())
6934  return emitOpError("expects number of results to match maskable operation "
6935  "number of results");
6936 
6937  if (!llvm::equal(maskableOp->getResults(), terminator.getOperands()))
6938  return emitOpError("expects all the results from the MaskableOpInterface "
6939  "to match all the values returned by the terminator");
6940 
6941  if (!llvm::equal(maskableOp->getResultTypes(), getResultTypes()))
6942  return emitOpError(
6943  "expects result type to match maskable operation result type");
6944 
6945  if (llvm::count_if(maskableOp->getResultTypes(),
6946  [](Type t) { return llvm::isa<VectorType>(t); }) > 1)
6947  return emitOpError("multiple vector results not supported");
6948 
6949  // Mask checks.
6950  Type expectedMaskType = maskableOp.getExpectedMaskType();
6951  if (getMask().getType() != expectedMaskType)
6952  return emitOpError("expects a ")
6953  << expectedMaskType << " mask for the maskable operation";
6954 
6955  // Passthru checks.
6956  Value passthru = getPassthru();
6957  if (passthru) {
6958  if (!maskableOp.supportsPassthru())
6959  return emitOpError(
6960  "doesn't expect a passthru argument for this maskable operation");
6961 
6962  if (maskableOp->getNumResults() != 1)
6963  return emitOpError("expects result when passthru argument is provided");
6964 
6965  if (passthru.getType() != maskableOp->getResultTypes()[0])
6966  return emitOpError("expects passthru type to match result type");
6967  }
6968 
6969  return success();
6970 }
6971 
6972 /// Folds empty `vector.mask` with no passthru operand and with or without
6973 /// return values. For example:
6974 ///
6975 /// %0 = vector.mask %mask { vector.yield %a : vector<8xf32> } :
6976 /// vector<8xi1> -> vector<8xf32>
6977 /// %1 = user_op %0 : vector<8xf32>
6978 ///
6979 /// becomes:
6980 ///
6981 /// %0 = user_op %a : vector<8xf32>
6982 ///
6983 /// Empty `vector.mask` with passthru operand are handled by the canonicalizer
6984 /// as it requires creating new operations.
6985 
6986 static LogicalResult foldEmptyMaskOp(MaskOp maskOp, MaskOp::FoldAdaptor adaptor,
6987  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
6988  if (!maskOp.isEmpty() || maskOp.hasPassthru())
6989  return failure();
6990 
6991  Block *block = maskOp.getMaskBlock();
6992  auto terminator = cast<vector::YieldOp>(block->front());
6993  if (terminator.getNumOperands() == 0) {
6994  // `vector.mask` has no results, just remove the `vector.mask`.
6995  return success();
6996  }
6997 
6998  // `vector.mask` has results, propagate the results.
6999  llvm::append_range(results, terminator.getOperands());
7000  return success();
7001 }
7002 
7003 LogicalResult MaskOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
7004  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &results) {
7005  if (succeeded(foldEmptyMaskOp(*this, adaptor, results)))
7006  return success();
7007 
7008  MaskFormat maskFormat = getMaskFormat(getMask());
7009  if (maskFormat != MaskFormat::AllTrue)
7010  return failure();
7011 
7012  // Move maskable operation outside of the `vector.mask` region.
7013  Operation *maskableOp = getMaskableOp();
7014  maskableOp->dropAllUses();
7015  maskableOp->moveBefore(getOperation());
7016 
7017  llvm::append_range(results, maskableOp->getResults());
7018  return success();
7019 }
7020 
7021 /// Canonialize empty `vector.mask` operations that can't be handled in
7022 /// `VectorMask::fold` as they require creating new operations.
7023 ///
7024 /// Example 1: Empty `vector.mask` with passthru operand.
7025 ///
7026 /// %0 = vector.mask %mask, %passthru { vector.yield %a : vector<8xf32> } :
7027 /// vector<8xi1> -> vector<8xf32>
7028 ///
7029 /// becomes:
7030 ///
7031 /// %0 = arith.select %mask, %a, %passthru : vector<8xf32>
7032 ///
7033 class CanonializeEmptyMaskOp : public OpRewritePattern<MaskOp> {
7034  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
7035 
7036  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(MaskOp maskOp,
7037  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
7038  if (!maskOp.isEmpty())
7039  return failure();
7040 
7041  if (!maskOp.hasPassthru())
7042  return failure();
7043 
7044  Block *block = maskOp.getMaskBlock();
7045  auto terminator = cast<vector::YieldOp>(block->front());
7046  assert(terminator.getNumOperands() == 1 &&
7047  "expected one result when passthru is provided");
7048 
7049  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<arith::SelectOp>(
7050  maskOp, maskOp.getResultTypes(), maskOp.getMask(),
7051  terminator.getOperand(0), maskOp.getPassthru());
7052 
7053  return success();
7054  }
7055 };
7056 
7057 void MaskOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
7058  MLIRContext *context) {
7059  results.add<CanonializeEmptyMaskOp>(context);
7060 }

7064 /// Returns the operation masked by this 'vector.mask'.
7065 Operation *MaskOp::getMaskableOp() {
7066  Block *block = getMaskBlock();
7067  if (block->getOperations().size() < 2)
7068  return nullptr;
7069 
7070  return &block->front();
7071 }

7076 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7077 // ScanOp
7078 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7079 
7080 LogicalResult ScanOp::verify() {
7081  VectorType srcType = getSourceType();
7082  VectorType initialType = getInitialValueType();
7083  // Check reduction dimension < rank.
7084  int64_t srcRank = srcType.getRank();
7085  int64_t reductionDim = getReductionDim();
7086  if (reductionDim >= srcRank)
7087  return emitOpError("reduction dimension ")
7088  << reductionDim << " has to be less than " << srcRank;
7089 
7090  // Check that rank(initial_value) = rank(src) - 1.
7091  int64_t initialValueRank = initialType.getRank();
7092  if (initialValueRank != srcRank - 1)
7093  return emitOpError("initial value rank ")
7094  << initialValueRank << " has to be equal to " << srcRank - 1;
7095 
7096  // Check shapes of initial value and src.
7097  ArrayRef<int64_t> srcShape = srcType.getShape();
7098  ArrayRef<int64_t> initialValueShapes = initialType.getShape();
7099  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedShape;
7100  for (int i = 0; i < srcRank; i++) {
7101  if (i != reductionDim)
7102  expectedShape.push_back(srcShape[i]);
7103  }
7104  if (!llvm::equal(initialValueShapes, expectedShape)) {
7105  return emitOpError("incompatible input/initial value shapes");
7106  }
7107 
7108  // Verify supported reduction kind.
7109  Type eltType = getDestType().getElementType();
7110  if (!isSupportedCombiningKind(getKind(), eltType))
7111  return emitOpError("unsupported reduction type ")
7112  << eltType << " for kind '" << stringifyCombiningKind(getKind())
7113  << "'";
7114 
7115  return success();
7116 }
7117 
7118 void mlir::vector::populateVectorToVectorCanonicalizationPatterns(
7119  RewritePatternSet &patterns, PatternBenefit benefit) {
7120  patterns
7121  .add<CreateMaskFolder, MaskedLoadFolder, MaskedStoreFolder, GatherFolder,
7122  ScatterFolder, ExpandLoadFolder, CompressStoreFolder,
7123  StridedSliceConstantMaskFolder, TransposeFolder>(
7124  patterns.getContext(), benefit);
7125 }

7161 
7162 Value mlir::vector::makeArithReduction(OpBuilder &b, Location loc,
7163  CombiningKind kind, Value v1, Value acc,
7164  arith::FastMathFlagsAttr fastmath,
7165  Value mask) {
7166  Type t1 = getElementTypeOrSelf(v1.getType());
7167  Type tAcc = getElementTypeOrSelf(acc.getType());
7168  Value result;
7169 
7170  switch (kind) {
7171  case CombiningKind::ADD:
7172  if (t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex())
7173  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AddIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7174  else if (llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc))
7175  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AddFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7176  else
7177  llvm_unreachable("invalid value types for ADD reduction");
7178  break;
7179  case CombiningKind::AND:
7180  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7181  result = b.createOrFold<arith::AndIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7182  break;
7183  case CombiningKind::MAXNUMF:
7184  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7185  "expected float values");
7186  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxNumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7187  break;
7188  case CombiningKind::MAXIMUMF:
7189  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7190  "expected float values");
7191  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaximumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7192  break;
7193  case CombiningKind::MINNUMF:
7194  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7195  "expected float values");
7196  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinNumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7197  break;
7198  case CombiningKind::MINIMUMF:
7199  assert(llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc) &&
7200  "expected float values");
7201  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinimumFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7202  break;
7203  case CombiningKind::MAXSI:
7204  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7205  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxSIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7206  break;
7207  case CombiningKind::MINSI:
7208  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7209  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinSIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7210  break;
7211  case CombiningKind::MAXUI:
7212  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7213  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MaxUIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7214  break;
7215  case CombiningKind::MINUI:
7216  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7217  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MinUIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7218  break;
7219  case CombiningKind::MUL:
7220  if (t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex())
7221  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MulIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7222  else if (llvm::isa<FloatType>(t1) && llvm::isa<FloatType>(tAcc))
7223  result = b.createOrFold<arith::MulFOp>(loc, v1, acc, fastmath);
7224  else
7225  llvm_unreachable("invalid value types for MUL reduction");
7226  break;
7227  case CombiningKind::OR:
7228  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7229  result = b.createOrFold<arith::OrIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7230  break;
7231  case CombiningKind::XOR:
7232  assert(t1.isIntOrIndex() && tAcc.isIntOrIndex() && "expected int values");
7233  result = b.createOrFold<arith::XOrIOp>(loc, v1, acc);
7234  break;
7235  };
7236 
7237  assert(result && "unknown CombiningKind");
7238  return selectPassthru(b, mask, result, acc);
7239 }

7241 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7242 // StepOp
7243 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7244 
7245 void StepOp::inferResultRanges(ArrayRef<ConstantIntRanges> argRanges,
7246  SetIntRangeFn setResultRanges) {
7247  auto resultType = cast<VectorType>(getType());
7248  if (resultType.isScalable()) {
7249  return;
7250  }
7251  unsigned bitwidth = ConstantIntRanges::getStorageBitwidth(resultType);
7252  APInt zero(bitwidth, 0);
7253  APInt high(bitwidth, resultType.getDimSize(0) - 1);
7254  ConstantIntRanges result = {zero, high, zero, high};
7255  setResultRanges(getResult(), result);
7256 }

7262 /// Create the vector.yield-ended region of a vector.mask op with `maskableOp`
7263 /// as masked operation.
7264 void mlir::vector::createMaskOpRegion(OpBuilder &builder,
7265  Operation *maskableOp) {
7266  assert(maskableOp->getBlock() && "MaskableOp must be inserted into a block");
7267  Block *insBlock = builder.getInsertionBlock();
7268  // Create a block and move the op to that block.
7269  insBlock->getOperations().splice(
7270  insBlock->begin(), maskableOp->getBlock()->getOperations(), maskableOp);
7271  YieldOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(), maskableOp->getResults());
7272 }
7273 
7274 /// Creates a vector.mask operation around a maskable operation. Returns the
7275 /// vector.mask operation if the mask provided is valid. Otherwise, returns
7276 /// the maskable operation itself.
7277 Operation *mlir::vector::maskOperation(OpBuilder &builder,
7278  Operation *maskableOp, Value mask,
7279  Value passthru) {
7280  if (!mask)
7281  return maskableOp;
7282  if (passthru)
7283  return MaskOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(),
7284  maskableOp->getResultTypes(), mask, passthru,
7285  maskableOp, createMaskOpRegion);
7286  return MaskOp::create(builder, maskableOp->getLoc(),
7287  maskableOp->getResultTypes(), mask, maskableOp,
7288  createMaskOpRegion);
7289 }
7290 
7291 /// Creates a vector select operation that picks values from `newValue` or
7292 /// `passthru` for each result vector lane based on `mask`. This utility is used
7293 /// to propagate the pass-thru value of vector.mask or for cases where only the
7294 /// pass-thru value propagation is needed. VP intrinsics do not support
7295 /// pass-thru values and every mask-out lane is set to poison. LLVM backends are
7296 /// usually able to match op + select patterns and fold them into a native
7297 /// target instructions.
7298 Value mlir::vector::selectPassthru(OpBuilder &builder, Value mask,
7299  Value newValue, Value passthru) {
7300  if (!mask)
7301  return newValue;
7302 
7303  return arith::SelectOp::create(builder, newValue.getLoc(), newValue.getType(),
7304  mask, newValue, passthru);
7305 }
